title: saucy burgers
directions: Mix beef with egg, onion, bread crumbs, ketchup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties, 1-inch thick.
Brown in large skillet for 5 minutes on each side.
Remove patties; drain fat.
Stir soup and water into skillet and bring to a boil.
Return patties to skillet, cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line large shallow baking pan to aluminum foil.
Cut wings at each joint.
Discard tips.
Melt margarine in lined pan.
Combine flour, onion, salt and pepper in bowl.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time, and shake to coat. Place in pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Turn wings over and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Transfer to serving platter.
Serve to barbecue sauce, Blue cheese dressing, buttermilk Ranch dressing or hot sauce.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Line pan in this order:
Broccoli, cheese, chicken and bread crumbs.

title: my favorite chicken pie(serves 6)
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add carrots, peas, onions, mushrooms and potatoes.
Mix broth, soup and cheese. Heat and pour over chicken mixture.
Make batter of flour, melted margarine, pepper and buttermilk.
Mix and pour evenly over top. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt on pork chops and brown.
Discard fat in pan. Add the sliced onion.
Mix sugar, catsup, vinegar and water.
Pour over chops.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until sauce has thickened.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef with onions in oil in a heavy pan.
Add about 2 cups boiling water and simmer until meat is tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put all ingredients in double boiler; beat continuously over boiling water for 7 minutes.

title: potluck chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and green peppers.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings to taste.
Add celery, black olives and mushrooms to liquid mixture.
Boil chicken breast halves.
Cook spaghetti in the broth-water left from cooking chicken.
Debone chicken and cut into large pieces.
Place in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole.
Add spaghetti.
Pour sauce and 2 cups of broth over all.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mistake bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients; mix just until moist and no lumps.
Bake in a 10 x 10 x 2-inch greased pan until brown at 450°.

title: apple tuna salad
directions: Toss together with mayonnaise or salad dressing thinned with juice from pineapple.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and pepper.
Layer alternately with tortillas, which have been dipped into hot chicken broth just long enough to soften, in a shallow 3-quart greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with chili powder and garlic salt. Spoon over chicken soup, mushroom soup and tomatoes, which have been broken up into smaller pieces.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until hot.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Mix egg yolks with sugar; add flour, baking powder and rind. Beat in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Grease pan; bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
After cool, slice cake in thirds to make 3 layers. (Use lasagna size pan.)

title: golden lemon cheese pie
directions: In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon brand and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Top with Golden Lemon Topping.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: snow cone syrup
directions: Bring sugar and water to full boil.
Remove from heat and add Kool-Aid.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
On a hot day, pour some over crushed ice for a cool treat.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix with flour and egg.
Form into patties and fry in hot oil.

title: bess' vegetable soup
directions: Note:
Try to use all fresh vegetables.

title: salsa mac 'n' beef
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add broth. Heat to boiling.
Stir in macaroni.
Reduce to medium heat.
Cook 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup and salsa.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: meat loaf patties
directions: Make a little well in the center of meat.
Cut the buttered bread in small diced pieces.
Add milk to dampen bread.
Add egg, beaten.
Add diced onion, using about half.
Add allspice and tomato paste.
Make out into 4 large patties and fry in a little olive oil.

title: peach bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla; add bread and drained peaches.
In small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Reserve 1 1/2 teaspoons of sugar mixture; set aside. Add remaining sugar mixture to peach mixture; mix well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually stir in chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: killer cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in large mixing bowl.
Chop beef, olives, mushrooms and green onions in blender or food processor.
(I put ingredients in blender separately, chop it, then add it to the bowl of cream cheese.)
You can use part of the "green" in the green onions if you like.
I always do.

title: low-sodium, low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish with fork until smooth. Bake about 25 minutes at 375°.
Ice in pan or serve plain to save calories.

title: cheesy snackeroos(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Prepare in a Dutch oven.
Prepare the corn bread or corn muffin mix according to package instructions.
Add to this mixture 1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Place in a well-greased Dutch oven. Sprinkle over the top the peanuts, 1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Melt the margarine in a separate can; drizzle over the top.
Cover Dutch oven; bake over coals for 25 minutes, or until light brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken; remove from broth and cut in small pieces. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Mix chicken, mushrooms (cut in small pieces), pimento, bell pepper and almonds. Mix with spaghetti and moisten all with cream of mushroom soup. Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried green tomato lasagne
directions: In a large sauce pan, combine the ripe tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, Italian seasoning, garlic, garlic salt and pepper. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; set aside. In a large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine. Dip green tomatoes slices in flour; brown

in skillet on both sides. Remove to paper towels to drain. Spoon 3/4 c. tomato mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Top with a third of the green tomatoes; sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. parmesan cheese. Repeat layers twice. Top with remaining tomato mixture and mozzarella cheese. Bake uncovered, at 350° for 15-20 minutes or until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: holiday hot tea special
directions: Mix all ingredients in container that contains a lid for storage for future use.
Use 3 to 4 teaspoons of mixture per hot cup of water.

title: diabetic apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add butter, vanilla, eggs, sugar substitute and blend well.
Stir in grated apples and walnuts. Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 375° for 40-45 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and juice.
Add fruit cocktail and pecans. Mix and pour into pie crust and chill.
Top with whole cherries and pecans.

title: white chocolate cheesecake(no bake)
directions: Crush graham crackers--add melted butter and mix together. Pour into 9 inch spring form pan and press onto bottom. Place crust in over at 375 degree for approximately 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: mount vernon's glazed carrots
directions: Drain liquid from carrots into saucepan; reserve carrots. Blend in orange juice, cinnamon, sugar, butter and vanilla. Bring to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring continuously, until sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add carrots and let sit 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
The hot sauce will heat and glaze carrots.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Core, peel and slice applies to bite size pieces.
In Dutch oven combine apple juice (thawed), butter, and cinnamon.
Mix cornstarch with 1 Tbsp. cold water to add to mixture on stove. Bring all ingredients to a good boil.
Add apples at once, thoroughly coat and turn off burner.
Filling is ready to put into shell and bake, or freeze for later use.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.
While warm, fill freezer bags with pineapple and liquid.
Seal and freeze.
Fill hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Distribute evenly.
Process in boiling bath 20 minutes for pints and 25 minutes for quarts.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook zucchini, onion and margarine in frying pan until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.

title: bobbie's picnic banana cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the oleo and sugar. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix bananas and buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Spread marshmallows evenly over greased pan.
Pour in batter and spread to edge.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rolled wheat cake
directions: Pour water over wheat or oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, rolled wheat and then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Cook pudding.
Let cool thoroughly.
Mix cake mix with pudding.
Spread mixture in pan.
Sprinkle top with morsels and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: diced potatoes with cumin
directions: Clean and dice potatoes.
Heat oil in a nonstick pan or wok over medium heat.
Add mustard seed and cumin.
Brown for 1 minute then add potatoes.
Then sprinkle turmeric and stir occasionally for the next 15 minutes.
When potatoes are lightly brown and almost done, add coriander, chili powder, pepper and salt.
Stir and cool for 1 to 2 minutes more.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Brown meat and onion until brown; drain off fat.
Add can of mushroom soup and can of chicken soup until well mixed.
Cook potatoes and mash; add butter, salt and pepper.
Put meat in casserole and top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.
This freezes well also.

title: one pot meal
directions: Make patties out of ground beef.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on each one.
In a large Dutch oven or pot, place a layer of patties. Add a layer of all vegetables.
Repeat layers until you have used all ingredients.
Mix ketchup, mustard and water; pour over top. Cook on medium until it starts to boil.
Turn stove on low heat; cook for 1 1/2 hours.
May need to add more water, depending on stove variations.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cream together butter, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Blend in the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Shape dough by rounded spoonfuls into balls. Mix the sugar and the cinnamon. Roll balls of dough in mixture. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set but not too hard. Remove immediately from baking sheets. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Saute short ribs and onion in hot fat until brown.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt; set aside.
Beat together the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, and milk; beat after each egg.
Alternately add flour mixture and banana, beating until smooth after each. May fold in 1/4 cup nuts, if desired.
Pour into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: san francisco firehouse bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add to milk with yeast, honey, salt and herbs.
Mix in cornmeal and 2 cups flour, beating well.
Add remaining flour and knead 3 to 5 minutes.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Divide in half and shape into oval loaves.
Place in 2 well-greased 1-pound coffee cans.
Let rise until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covering loosely with foil during the last 15 minutes.

title: murrell's whipped cream topped jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple.
When cool, add bananas.

title: sausage balls
directions: Wet hands to mix ingredients.
Keep hands wet to shape balls. Bake at 350° for half hour.

title: cranberry raisin loaf
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch loaf pan.
Mix first 8 ingredients. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Add dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Spoon into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: candied walnuts
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar and sour cream.
Bring to a boil on low heat for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts to this mixture.
Stir until nuts are coated.
Spread on waxed paper, turning once to dry.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for first 10 minutes and 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together.
You can mix this cake with a spoon.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter in a greased sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Add chicken cubes and mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix crackers, poppy seed and butter. Spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: bible verse brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except dry ???, baking powder and cocoa.
Combine these 3 ingredients and stir into wet ingredients. Spread into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cut into bars while still warm.
You may sprinkle the top with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Mash squash; add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin date bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift remaining ingredients; stir in nuts and dates.
Pour in two pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick chili supper
directions: In a 2-quart microwavable dish, cook hamburger and onion, covered, for 6 minutes on High.
Break up hamburger; cover and cook 4 more minutes.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Stir, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on High or until melted.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all in saucepan, heating on low.
Stir constantly until dough pulls away from side of pan.
Cool.
Knead until smooth. Store in airtight container.
Can be tripled.

title: cheddar cornsticks and muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour with cornmeal, baking powder, cheese and bacon.
Combine remaining ingredients in separated bowl; beat well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full or well-greased and heated heavy cornstick pan, filling almost full.
Bake muffins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes and corn sticks at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chow-chow pickle
directions: Mix dry ingredients and wet with vinegar.
Put in all chopped vegetables and cook until done.
Add some hot green peppers or red shake pepper.
Keep stirred, it will stick.

title: white sugar christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown onions in hot cooking fat.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Season to taste.
Pour into well oiled baking dish. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Place cut up chicken in a big casserole dish.
Add all the ingredients; mix.
Let boil and simmer until chicken is cooked.
Add 2 tablespoons oil, if desired.
Serve with steamed rice!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt and leaving slightly undercooked; drain. Combine egg whites, skim milk, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, salt, white pepper and parsley and blend well. Mix sauce with macaroni and spoon into 1-quart baking dish sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits 1 tube at a time. Shake in sack with sugar and cinnamon. Put in tub pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Heat margarine, brown sugar and water in saucepan. Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine the cornstarch and sugar.
Add the beet water, vinegar, salt and bring to a boil, stirring until thick and smooth.
Add the beets and cook over a low fire for 20 minutes. When ready to serve, add the butter and bring to a boil.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix onions, celery, peppers and garlic with some of the fat taken from broth.
Add lump of butter.
Saute until lightly browned.
Add broth, tomato paste and mushroom soup.
Cook slowly 40 minutes.
Add diced chicken and heat 10 minutes or so.

title: double decker fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, sour cream, butter and salt. Butter sides of pan and mix cocoa and water and stir into saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil until 238° on a candy thermometer or until a small amount of syrup when dropped into cold water, forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in nuts and beat until mixture thickens.
Spread into a foil lined 8-inch square pan.
In a saucepan, combine condensed milk and chips.
Stir until smooth and melted.
Spread mixture evenly over cocoa fudge. Chill until firm.
Using foil, pull from pan and cut into squares.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Then add tiny shrimp by hand.
Chill.

title: beet jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Add beets and pineapple; stir well and pour into individual serving cups or serving dish.
Unmold cups on lettuce leaf, if desired.

title: stuffed mushrooms gazpacho style
directions: Partially peel a cucumber and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Top each slice with 1 teaspoon creamed cottage cheese.
Garnish each with a parsley sprig and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Contains about 6 calories each.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow dish.
In another dish, combine milk and oil.
Dip chicken pieces into milk mixture, then roll in the Parmesan mixture. Place chicken, skin side up, in a shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except whipped cream.
Add cream last, gently folding together.
Chill at least an hour.

title: razzle dazzle quick jam
directions: In a medium bowl, crush raspberries to measure 2 cups.
Finely chop cherries to measure 1 cup.
In a 4-quart bowl, combine crushed raspberries, chopped cherries, sugar, corn syrup and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, add water to reserved cherry liquid to measure 3/4 cup.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Line pan with pie pastry.
Place sliced fresh peaches in pie shell.
Mix together sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and cream; pour over peaches.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn, eggs, milk, 3/4 cup cracker crumbs, butter, sugar, onion, salt and pepper.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: cheese salad
directions: Make jello; let set until thick.
Then add fruit and marshmallows.
When set, spread with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with 1/2 pound grated sharp cheese and crushed nuts.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Put chicken in a pot.
Cover chicken with water.
Add several pieces of fatback.
Add desired salt and pepper to stock.
Add one stick of butter.

title: chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken breast, mayonnaise, Cool Whip and onion overnight. Mix together and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Spoon mixture into a bowl; cover and chill.
Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add almonds, sunflower kernels and noodles, tossing occasionally.
Spoon mixture into a large bowl; cover and chill.
Add vinegar mixture to noodle mixture; let stand 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, carrots and onions, tossing to coat. Yield:
12 servings.

title: dinosaur cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat the margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed, about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add about half of the flour, sugar and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low to medium speed until thoroughly combined, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally.
Then beat or stir in the remaining flour.
Shape cookies into dinosaurs.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 large cookies.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place stick of margarine in deep casserole.
Melt in oven. Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour over melted margarine.
Combine berries and sugar and pour into batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream balls
directions: You will need an ice cream scoop, measuring spoons, square baking pan and 4 plates.

title: lemon veal with spinach
directions: Brown veal in oil in a large heavy skillet.
Add chopped onion, cooking until onion is tender.
Pour off the fat.
Add water, lemon juice, pepper and crushed fennel seed.
Cover and simmer over low heat 1 hour or until veal is tender, stirring occasionally.
More water may be added if needed. Add green onions and spinach. Cover and continue simmering until spinach is tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Arrange veal on warm serving platter surrounded with a border of spinach. Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add onion or leek; cover and cook 10 minutes (5 minutes for shallot or green onions), stirring occasionally.
Add cauliflower; cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Pour in enough stock, milk or water to barely cover ingredients.
Cover pan partially and bring to boil.
Let boil until cauliflower is tender, about 10 minutes.
Transfer to blender or processor and puree or pass through fine disk of food mill.
Thin soup with cream and season with salt and pepper.
Stir in Port.
Serve.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water; mix together until smooth.
Mix dry ingredients together; combine with sugar mixture.
Pour into floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan or sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You will also need cooking spray.

title: grandma's favorite gingerbread
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients. Cream together shortening and sugar. Add molasses and mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup dry ingredients. Beat in egg.
Add remaining dry ingredients alternately with boiling water.
Beat 1/2 minute.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured 8 x 12-inch pan; bake 45 to 50 minutes in moderate 350° oven.
After it is cooled, frost or serve with whipped cream or fruit.

title: date nut muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to butter and egg mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add orange rind, dates and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured muffin tins.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes until brown.
Glaze while still hot.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix egg, pepper, salt, bread crumbs, hamburger, onion and 1/4 cup of undiluted soup.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook's Note:
Use crackers such as Ritz or Town House.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 3/4-inch cubes.
Season with salt and soy sauce. Roll in all-purpose flour.
Roll again in beaten egg yolks.
Roll again in flour.
Deep fry in wok until done.
Cut tomato into 8 parts.
Cut onion into 8 parts.
Chop green pepper into 3/4-inch squares.
When pork is done, drain it.
Using the wok, brown the onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon of oil for 30 seconds.
Add sweet and sour sauce and cook for 1 minute.
Add tomato and pineapple chunks; cook about five seconds.
Add the deep fried pork and take away from the heat and serve immediately.

title: molasses blueberry cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Put peeled, sliced peaches in shallow 2 quart baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix flour and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender or fingers until crumbly.
Press over peaches.
Bake at 375 for 25 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Serve warm with cream.

title: chef's salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, place the lettuce, green pepper, celery, cucumber, radishes and tomatoes.
Arrange eggs, meat and cheese on top of vegetables.
Pour French dressing or dressing of your choice over the salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Spray a saucepan with Pam.
Saute vegetables for 5 minutes. Add 3 cups water; stir well.
Add spices and bouillon and boil. Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Add to soup, stirring.
Add Butter Buds and lemon juice.
Blend well.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add milk, dry milk, clams and liquid.
Blend well.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir meat, green beans and soup together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Put single layer of Tater Tots on top.
Place cheese on top if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Whip together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients.
Remove.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on thin slice of lunch meat.
Wrap around a whole dill pickle.
Slice into bite size slices.

title: grilled linkburgers
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Divide into 8 portions.
Pat one portion around each sausage link.

title: chop and potato scallop
directions: Dredge chops in seasoned flour and brown in a small amount of butter or oil.
Alternate layers of potatoes and onion in a buttered shallow baking dish.
Cover with cream sauce and top with browned chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil and continue to bake until tender.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat 4 egg whites.
Add sugar.
Separately beat until light lemon color 4 egg yolks.
Fold egg yolks into egg white mixture. Add vanilla.
Slowly add 3/4 cup flour.
Pour onto greased and floured deep cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes. Loosen all sides.
Place damp towel over top.
Draw towel lightly across cake and turn over.
Fold ends and sides of damp towel back over cake for 2 to 3 minutes to steam crust.
Spread with jam or custard filling.
By lifting side of towel, roll up until it is on the bottom. Wrap towel around roll.
Let stand 12 to 15 minutes. Unwrap; cover with sifted powdered sugar.

title: citrus marinade
directions: Mix orange juice, lemon juice, garlic and oregano.
Marinate pork for at least 30 minutes before cooking.
Discard the marinade after using.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy italian lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions; drain.
In skillet, cook ground chuck until brown; drain off excess fat. Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, sour cream, green onion and green pepper.
Put half of the lasagna noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered baking dish.
Moisten lasagna with some meat sauce.
Cover with cheese mixture; top with remaining lasagna, then meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes. Allow to stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, gently combine potatoes and eggs. Combine dry ingredients and onion; stir into potato mixture. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a preheated, greased skillet.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Serve with applesauce.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in buttered casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, shortening, margarine, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: fresh strawberry jam
directions: Add the Sure-Jell to the strawberries; stir and let stand 20 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Pack in glass jars and put in freezer.

title: thick vegetable soup
directions: Cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven the beef cubes and water.
Add remaining ingredients; cook until vegetables are tender and done. Add more water to make a medium consistency of soup.

title: creole beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over meat; brown in hot shortening.
Add hot water; cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Add vegetables about 30 minutes before cooking time is finished.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on the back of box.
In the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan, melt margarine.
Rub sides of pan with margarine so the batter will not stick to sides of pan. Then sprinkle brown sugar over the margarine.
Lay pineapple rings on sugar and pour the batter on the pineapple.
Bake as directed on box.

title: "no-fat" cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, broth and water in saucepan.
Simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.
Pour into blender or beat by hand until smooth.
Return to pan and bring to boiling.
Stir in milk. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and chives on top.
Serves 8.

title: orange glazed pecans
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour, milk, margarine and syrup.	Cook to soft ball
on candy thermometer.
Add orange juice and orange rind. Cook again to soft ball.
Pour over pecan halves.
Stir until well coated.
Pour on wax paper and separate.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, soup, sour cream, butter, salt, pepper and 1 cup cheese together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cottage cheese jello
directions: Beat each separately before mixing together. Chill and serve.

title: chilled strawberry soup from disney world
directions: Place strawberries in a blender or food processor.
Process until well blended.
Remove to bowl and add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Mix cake mix and oil in large bowl.
Add 7-Up and mix.
Add eggs, then pudding mix.
Pour in greased and floured cake pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice(the best from new mexico kitchens cookbook)
directions: Chop onion and pepper and mince garlic.
Saute in olive oil until onion is transparent.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer, tightly covered, on lowest heat for about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown venison in butter.
Add onion and garlic and cook for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: apple coffeecake
directions: Cream together shortening and 1 cup sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, soda and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in chopped apples. Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts evenly over batter. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut cake icing(aunt cleo casey)
directions: Cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly, until it turns yellow or forms a soft ball.
Pour over layers and add coconut.

title: hot rolls (quick)
directions: Dissolve water, salt and sugar and mix well.
Add yeast crumbled into 1 cup flour; mix well.
Add to water mixture, then add shortening and 2 more cups flour.
This may be mixed at 9 o'clock, let rise, make into rolls about 11 o'clock and ready for oven or for noon.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain juices off green beans.
Mix beans, milk and soup in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 can of dried onions.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Pour rest of onions on top and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Place the egg in boiling water and simmer 1 minute.
Cool under cold running water.
Drop garlic through feed tube while machine is running.
Process until minced.
Add rest of ingredients and process 8 to 10 seconds.
Mix salad just before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients but butter and pecans. Melt butter; add to mix.
Add pecans.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: diet soup
directions: Any meat chopped fine can be added, as long as it is lean. That would add some calories.
Simmer until cabbage is done.

title: zucchini filled burritos
directions: Cook zucchini, chilies, onion, garlic and seasoning in 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and wheat germ.
Stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.

title: hot beef spread
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature and mix with sour cream, then stir in other ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Best served with French bread.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet to hot gelatin mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart ring mold and chill until set. Drained off juices may be substituted for part of the boiling water.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Layer tortillas, chicken, onion, soup and cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Freezes well.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together egg, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and then apple and nuts.
Pour into a greased 8-inch pie plate or square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.
Good warm or cold.

title: marinated italian chicken breasts(low-fat)
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan; pour dressing over.
Marinate for at least 15 minutes, the longer the better, in refrigerator. Place chicken on rack of broiler pan; broil for 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Reserve liquid and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Pour into 2-quart saucepan.
Add milk, 4 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat at once and immediately stir in mashed potato flakes.
Stir in sour cream, sharp cheese and onion.

title: pear cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix flour and sugar together; add milk.
Pour into casserole dish.
Spoon in pears and juice over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease 2 large loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients with mixer until blended.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° or until golden brown. (Sometimes it takes over an hour.)
Test with toothpick.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Pour Glaze over bread while still in pan.
Leave in pans 1 hour before removing.

title: angel hair pasta
directions: Melt butter and saut onions, bell pepper and green onions until tender. Add crawfish or shrimp and cook approximately 10 minutes. Add soup and cook approximately 5 to 10 minutes. Add half and half until you reach desired consistency. Season with red pepper and Tony's seasoning. Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Serve over pasta or mix pasta and sauce together before serving.

title: sugar-free fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients; set aside for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Set oven at 300°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Blend in oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together and mix thoroughly.
Make into small balls; flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 350°. Makes about 11 dozen small or 7 to 8 dozen medium size cookies.

title: homemade soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 2 large baking sheets.
In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir with rubber spatula until well blended and yeast is dissolved.
Water temperature should be between 105° and 115°.
If water is too hot, will kill yeast.
With a wooden spoon, gradually stir in sugar, salt and enough flour (about 3 1/2 cups) until a soft and slightly sticky dough forms.

title: pat's mustard sauce
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Cook in double boiler about 5 minutes or until thick.
Delicious with ham or summer sausage.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: holly christmas cookies
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows; add vanilla and coloring.
Pour in corn flakes.
Drop by the spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet in the form of holly leaves.
Place 3 candies on each sprig of holly.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Beat sugar, egg, shortening and milk.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices and add to sugar mixture; beat.
Add cooked mincemeat. Put in 2 loaf pans.
Cook at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown 3/4 pound ground beef and drain.
Add 1/2 cup barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.

title: layer cake
directions: Mix and cook at 350° until done.

title: baked chicken-n-rice
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place in covered oven dish.
Add broth, soup and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: nanny's chocolate cake
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients together.
Sift sugar and flour. Mix eggs, buttermilk, salt and soda.
Fold together all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes or until done at 325°.

title: "souper" mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water.
Drain water.
Add mushroom soup, milk and cheese; then whip.
Mix and bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: irish colcannon
directions: Gently fry onion or leeks in melted butter or margarine until onions or leeks are soft.
Add milk to mashed potatoes and stir over low heat until heated through.
Mix potatoes, cabbage and onions or leeks together until mixture is fluffy.
Serve with ham or bacon.
Try it, you'll like it.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns in refrigerator; break into pieces. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add potatoes.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage; drain grease.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, pie filling and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at medium speed 2 minutes. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Spread half the batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half the sugar and cinnamon. Repeat layer.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Makes 12 servings.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: virginia's corn bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add oil, egg and just enough water to make a batter.
Bake in iron cornstick pans or an iron skillet that has been well-greased and hot.
While preheating the oven to 400°, heat the irons or skillet for they must be hot.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for cornsticks or 10 minutes in skillet (until browned). Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: In a bowl, beat the cream cheese and the Marshmallow Creme together. Use as a dip for your fruit.

title: bisquick
directions: Sift together dry ingredients three times.
Cut in shortening until it looks like coarse corn meal.
To measure, pile lightly into cup.

title: heavenly lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple, sour cream and pecans.
Let set.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture alternately with water.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in sauerkraut.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread over favorite bread.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix coconut and nuts together.
Sprinkle over the bottom of the pan.
Mix cake in a bowl according to the directions on the package. Pour into pan over coconut and nuts.
Beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth and creamy.
Sift powdered sugar and beat into cream cheese mixture until well mixed.
Spread over the top of cake.
Bake as time on box directs, adding 10 or 15 minutes.
Cool on a rack, cut and serve.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut dates, nuts and orange slices into small pieces.
Add coconut.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
In another bowl, mix eggs, sugar, flour, soda and milk.
Pour over nut mixture; beat well.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan. Cool upside down over bottle.

title: apricot streusel bars
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and salt.
Cut in 3/4 cup oleo with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in oats and blend thoroughly.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of this mixture for topping.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: In bowl combine powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter. Combine all together real good.
Then roll in small balls and flatten out a little.
Put enough chocolate in bottom of petit four cups then put the ball in and cover with chocolate.
Place in cool place to harden.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the mushrooms in margarine until golden. Add chicken broth with milk to measure 1 1/4 cups. Set aside. Blend flour into mushrooms, then gradually blend in broth, milk and half and half.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in Swiss cheese and stir until it melts. Fold in chicken. Season with salt and pepper.
Put vermicelli in greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with Parmesan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly and top is golden.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift first 8 ingredients together.
Blend in salad oil, pineapple and eggs and beat 4 minutes.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool and frost.

title: homemade soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and salt.
Gradually add flour. Roll dough into long rolls and shape pretzels.
Beat egg and brush on top. Sprinkle on salt. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Rub beef with seasoned flour or pound into steak with meat hammer.
Brown meat, onions and pepper in Crisco in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat until steak is tender (about 45 minutes).

title: kelli's rich, chewy brownies
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and butter in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave at High 2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in condensed milk and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly on a wire rack.

title: mel's impossible quiche
directions: *Can also use a 6 1/2 ounce can of well drained crab meat.

title: mediterranean pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Transfer crust to pizza pan.
Spread crust with sauce.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake 14 to 18 minutes or until crust is golden and cheese is bubbling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt; add shortening.
Blend until crumbly.
Add water, egg and vinegar; mix well.
Knead dough slightly.
Divide into 4 parts.
Yield: 4 (1 crust) pies or 2 (2 crust) pies. Yield: 8 servings.
Carbohydrate 24 g, protein 3 g, fat 19 g, calories 283.
One serving = 1 bread starch exchange, 3 fat exchange.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, about 20 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole bowl, break eggs and beat lightly.
Cut up both cheeses in chunks, add margarine.
Add cooked macaroni.
Add evaporated milk while stirring until all ingredients are covered.
Add paprika to garnish top and bake at 375° until brown on edges and top (about 35 minutes).

title: french coconut pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.* Place melted butter in large bowl. Reserve 3 tablespoons of the cake mix; set aside. Add remaining cake mix to butter; blend well. Add egg; mix well. Stir in oats. Press 2/3 of cake mix mixture (about 2 1/2 cups) in bottom of sprayed pan.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered baking dish.
Add beaten eggs last.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Set baking dish in water to cook.
Souffle is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ants on a log
directions: Wash the celery and cut into pieces (about 5-inches long). Spread peanut butter on the celery from one end to the other. Press raisins into peanut butter.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into glass dish or mold. Chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in diced apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8
x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with or without whipped cream or Cool Whip or ice cream.
Makes 8 to 9 servings.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° until top is brown, about 30 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Fry bacon and crumble,	add
onions and saute.	Put the seasoned tomatoes along with the
okra.
Add the water that is mixed with flour.
Add
tomato
sauce,
chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stew until the okra is well done.

title: fresh fruit compote
directions: I peel and pit peaches.
Core pear; cut peaches and pear lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Pit cherries if desired. Combine peaches, pears, cherries, pineapple and water in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave covered with lid at High power until fruit is almost tender throughout but not soft, 5 to 8 minutes of cooking.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion together.
Then add remaining ingredients and cook 1 hour over medium heat.

title: gourmet strawberries
directions: In mixer, blend coconut and 1 package jello.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Pinch shape to resemble strawberries.
Roll each in 2nd package of jello.
Dip plastic stems in Eagle milk to "glue" into strawberry.
Yields 40 each.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and flour together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat together eggs, syrup, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups pecans.
Pour over top of crust and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
(Bake until set in middle.)

title: mexican hominy
directions: Mix, heat and serve.

title: date torte
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together by hand.
Lightly grease and flour a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour. Test.
When cool, scoop out of pan and break up onto a torte plate; build into a mound.
Top with the drained pineapple; spread around mound.
Slice a banana and place over mound.
Top with Cool Whip.
Trim with halved maraschino cherries.
Serve by spoon.

title: simple sticky buns
directions: Cut each loaf of dough into 18 pieces. Arrange half in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon. In a saucepan over low heat, melt butter. Remove from heat. Stir in brown sugar, pudding mix and milk until smooth. Pour over dough. Sprinkle with pecans and raisins, if desired. Arrange remaining pieces of dough over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight or let stand at room temperature for 3 hours. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until center sounds hollow when tapped with fingers. Invert onto serving platter or baking sheet. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: all-bran pull apart bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients, except flour. Stir well and let rise until double, 1 hour.
Punch down and shape in oblong rolls.
Dip in melted butter.
Stack in greased tube pan and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortellini & veggie salad
directions: Cook veggies, and leave them a little crisp.
Cool veggies and tortellini.
Add other ingredients and add a jar of italian dressing. Cover and chill.	Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put first 6 ingredients on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle box of cake mix over filling.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Add chopped nuts over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: good tea cakes
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spray or grease cookie sheets; roll in small balls. Press with fork or hand.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(Put around 12 on each cookie sheet.)
Makes 36.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash into thick chunks and quarter; cook in saltwater just until done.
Drain well.
Melt butter and add to stuffing mix.
Combine soup and sour cream.
In large bowl, combine squash, carrots, onion and salt and pepper to taste; fold in soup mixture. In a 13 x 9 baking dish, spread a layer of stuffing mix and pour squash mixture over it.
Sprinkle top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until completely heated through.
May be prepared ahead of time and kept in the fridge until baking time.
Serves 12.

title: club crackers bars
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar until well blended; boil 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Line 9 x13-inch pan with Club House crackers.
After filling is cooled, spread on crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Melt the chips and frost on top of crackers.
Let cool.
Cut them at room temperature.

title: pat's potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This should be put in a greased casserole dish.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: 2 yogurt pies
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip and fill crusts; chill and serve. Low-fat but tasty.

title: peanut butter chocolate candy cookies
directions: Put mixture of the first 4 ingredients into a well-greased cookie sheet.
Pour the melted chocolate chips over the mixture. Refrigerate 15 minutes, then slice into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan (large cookie sheet size). Garnish with green peppers, tomatoes, lettuce, cheese, little green onions, black olives or whatever you desire.
Serve with nacho chips.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add
flour.
Fold
in
orange slices, coconut and nuts. Add fruit cocktail
very
gently.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan that's been greased
and
floured.
Bake at
250° for about 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix up pudding as directions indicate on box. Soften cream cheese; mix cheese, Cool Whip, vanilla flavoring and lemon juice together. Then take 1 row of cookies and crush; then begin to layer ingredients with 1/2 mix, another row of Oreo cookies and your last row should be Oreos on top.

title: cheese and cherry delight
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Beat well; set aside.
Prepare whipped topping mix according to package directions.
Fold in cream cheese mixture. Spread evenly over graham crust.
Spread pie filling.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine cream of mushroom soup and milk in saucepan; bring to boil.
Line 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Ritz crackers, then a layer of asparagus, then a layer of cheese.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over this.
Add another layer of crackers and cheese. Pour remainder of soup mixture over top.
Bake in oven at 400° until bubbly.

title: chewy butter cake
directions: Combine yellow cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Mix and pat into a cake pan.
Then beat the 2 remaining eggs, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix well and pour over crust in cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
(Top should be soft when you take cake out.)
Don't overbake!

title: aunt grace's chewy chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in 4 cup saucepan over low heat. Stir in sugar and corn syrup; add water.
Bring to a low boil and keep cooking over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring.
Off heat, add salt and vanilla.
Reheat in microwave.
Serve on ice cream or angel food cake.

title: meringue turtle doves
directions: Line cookie sheet with brown paper.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Put mixture in decorating bag with 1/2-inch round tip, filling bag half full. Beginning at head end, squeeze bag gently, moving tip clockwise direction to form a question mark.
For lower body, continue squeezing as you move tip about 2 1/2-inches to right, back left, then right, releasing pressure as you pull up tip.
Place mini chocolate pieces on head for eye and beak.
Bake in a 300° oven about 15 minutes.
Turn off oven and let cookies dry in oven with the door closed about 30 minutes.
Makes about 24.

title: cheese soup
directions: Add water to potatoes, celery, onion, parsley flakes, seasonings and bouillon cube.
Cover; cook until tender.
Blend flour with a small amount of milk; stir into vegetable mixture. Add remaining milk; cook until thickened.
Add Velveeta; stir until melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion, garlic and beef together.
Add tomato paste, mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Boil noodles.
Combine cheeses in bowl.
Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Layer noodles, meat and cheese.
Last layer should be noodles.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place chopped nuts in the bottom of Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in large bowl with lid.
Cut each biscuit into quarters. Put pieces in bowl of sugar mixture gradually (1 can at a time). Shake to coat.
Put biscuit pieces in pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour on biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out onto cake plate leaving pan over bread for 1 minute.
(The heat will loosen the brown sugar.) Eat with fingers.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant (round), saute hamburger with onions and add tomatoes.
Place layer of meat mixture in casserole dish; cover with layer of eggplant.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes.
Cook rice and serve casserole spooned over rice.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, combine 1 1/2 cups cheese with remaining ingredients.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 25 minutes until firm.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms and beans.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add mushrooms and beans with liquid. Heat and serve.

title: fresh pineapple delight
directions: Cut lengthwise slice from pineapple.
Remove about 1/3 of pineapple.
Scoop pulp from slice; discard rind.
Scoop pulp from remaining portion of pineapple, leaving shell about 1/2-inch thick.
Set aside.
Chop pineapple into bite size pieces.
Crush 1 cup of pineapple pieces.
Reserve rest for dipping.
Combine crushed pineapple and juice, egg, sugar and flour in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool.
Fold in whipping cream and pour into pineapple shell.
Serve dip with reserved pineapple and other fresh fruit cut into serving pieces.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed adding 1/3 cup cream and 3/4 cup margarine.
Pour half of batter in a greased oblong pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in 1/3 cup cream and spread on top of cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake about 30 minutes.
This cake requires no icing.
It is rich and moist.

title: louisiana crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a large iron pot.
Blend flour and stir over medium-low heat until roux is dark brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add onions, celery, green peppers and garlic and cook until tender-crisp, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice, and simmer 20 minutes.
Ladle etouffee into soup bowls and top each serving with 1/2 cup fluffy rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and flour and beat well. Add buttermilk and flavorings and mix. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chocolate 'n' oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In bowl combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Reserving 1/2 cup, press remaining oat mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and semi-sweet chips.
Top with remaining oat mixture.
Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix everything in a blender.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate, buttered. Bake until custard sets at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in the crock-pot on low. Great for cooking all day or until meat is done.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in large skillet and drain.
Add rest of ingredients except for cheese and spaghetti and mix well.
Put spaghetti in casserole.
Pour meat sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: toasted coconut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut in shallow baking pan. Bake 7 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned, shaking pan often to toast coconut evenly.
Set aside.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; set aside.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until it forms soft ball when dropped in cool water.
Add dates (cut up) and cook until it forms hard ball when dropped in cool water.
Take from heat and add pecans.
Beat until thick.
Pour out on damp cloth.
Roll in long round rolls (smaller rolls for smaller pieces of date loaf).
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Take out and cut in thin slices.

title: asparagus appetizer
directions: Cut the asparagus stalks to about 3-inch lengths and wrap the cut ends with ham strips.
Serve as a dip with Thousand Island dressing.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Bring butter and milk to a boil in saucepan.
Remove pan from heat and add the Baker's chocolate, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Spread frosting on cake.

title: pork chops with cheese
directions: Brush pork chops with tomato paste.
Mix cheese with bread crumbs; pat into chops.
Pan-fry chops until brown; place in baking dish.
Add a small amount of water to prevent sticking. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with sauce.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: prize coffee cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Top with mixture of 1/2 cup brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: french sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300° and grease an angel food or Bundt pan. Cream in bowl the 1 cup sugar, butter and eggs.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to ingredients the sour cream, milk and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine walnuts, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and mace.
In pan, divide sour cream mixture in half and pour half into pan.
Sprinkle nut mixture over this and cover with rest of sour cream mix.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack and invert for serving and slicing.

title: football party dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and party dip together. Stir in diced red peppers and diced black olives. Chill an hour. Using a spatula, form a football shape on a platter; chill 4 hours or overnight. Decorate football using vegetable slices and cheese strips. If you have to, look at a football.

title: playdough
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in oil and water.
Add more water as necessary to form a soft, pliable dough.
This dough keeps well in airtight container.

title: "nuts and bolts" party mix
directions: Mix cereals, peanuts, mixed nuts and pretzels together gently. Put on baking sheets or large roaster.
Drizzle melted oleo mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: fix ahead chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Discard drippings.
Stir soup, milk and seasonings together, heat. Add carrots and onions.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add lima beans and cook until separated, stirring often. Pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate immediately until 1 hour and 15 minutes before serving.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Decrease baking time, if covered, by 15 minutes if not refrigerated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with asparagus. Top with chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice together and pour over all.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crusty casserole bread loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, softened margarine and 3 cups flour.
Beat at low speed until blended. Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Mix in rest of flour by hand or mix all steps by hand.
Cover.
Let rise.
Stir down.
Beat for 1/2 minute.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: flemish carbonnades(a crock-pot recipe)
directions: Trim round steak.
Cut into serving portions.
Combine flour, sugar and pepper.
Toss steak to coat thoroughly.
Place potatoes in crock-pot and cover with steak pieces.
Thoroughly combine soup mix and beer.
Pour over steak, moistening well.
Cover and cook on low setting 8 to 12 hours.
Thicken gravy before serving.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions, omitting butter.
Turn into casserole.
Add butter and cheese and beat until well blended.
Add scallions and mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours for flavors to blend.
If desired, sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If casserole is not refrigerated, bake for only 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook Jiffy mix according to box directions.
Let cool.
Cut in half.
Crumble 1/2 corn bread in dish, then 1/2 cup tomatoes, 1/2 cup bell peppers and 1/2 cup onion.
Sprinkle 1/2 jar of bacon pieces.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare eggplant and cut in 1-inch cubes.	Cook in boiling salt water
for	10 minutes and drain.
Add next 8 ingredients and mix well.
Add	seasonings.
Pour in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with
sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 8 servings.

title: pickled eggs in beet juice
directions: In saucepan, boil young beets until tender.
Skin and cover with liquid made by combining brown sugar, vinegar, water, cinnamon and cloves.
Let beets stand in mixture for several days. Remove beets and add eggs.
Let stand for 2 days.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and shortening as you would for pie crust. Add sour milk, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Roll out and place a teaspoon of filling on each cut cookie.
Roll out a top and place over filling.
Pinch with fork to seal.
Bake at 375°.

title: spicy cranberry sauce
directions: Heat sauce until smooth; add cornstarch and spices and blend well.
Add water; cook over medium heat in small skillet, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and is thickened.
Add little franks or links.
Cook for 10 minutes until heated through.

title: chicken cashew salad
directions: Marinate chicken breasts for 4 to 5 hours in mixture of 2 cups pineapple juice, wine vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon ginger, honey, 2 teaspoons Worcestershire and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Then either bake it and cut it up or cut it up first and stir-fry it.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Blend in shortening and butter, 1/2 at a time until it looks like coarse corn meal. Use 3 or 4 Tbsp. ice water or milk to form dough.
Too much liquid will make it sticky.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.
Roll out on floured board to fit pie plate.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook onion in margarine but do not brown.
Blend in flour and heat until bubbly.
Add milk and stock and cook until sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add cheese. Stir until melted.
Add vegetables.
Heat.
You may top with parsley or chives to serve.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the sugar and butter.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until almost set.
Serve with whipped cream and strawberries, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
May be dipped as ice cream or cut into squares.
Any fruit may be used with pineapple.

title: gem dressing
directions: Cook sugar and water until it spins a thread; let cool. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add syrup and beat thoroughly. Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot frank dip
directions: Mix mustard and currant jelly.
Heat to simmering.
Stir in franks.
Keep hot.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add well beaten eggs. Mix vanilla wafers, coconut and nuts; pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: butter balls
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Roll into small balls (about the size
of
a very large marble).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool; roll in powdered sugar.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut large Spanish or Bermuda onions into 1/4-inch slices. Separate into rings.
Put flour in paper bag and shake so that the onion rings are coated with flour.
Then dip onion rings in batter and deep fry.

title: skillet beef supreme
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add
onion	and
green pepper.
Add celery and cut green
beans.
Cook
to	5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with soy sauce and water.
Add to skillet.	Stir in mushrooms. Cook about	10
minutes, stirring, until liquid is clear and shiny and
beans	are
tender.
Add salt as desired. Serve over cooked rice.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix next items together and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 60 minutes at 375°.
Serve with rice.

title: pork kilawin
directions: Boil pork liempo, in 2 cups water and some salt.
Cook until liempo is tender and skin easily peels off.
While hot, cut liempo into cubes.
Place in a bowl and add vinegar, soy sauce and chopped raw onions.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple and banana salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Mash softened cream cheese and gradually add lemon and pineapple juices.
Beat until creamy. Slice bananas (lengthwise) and spread with cheese mixture. Arrange on a bed of lettuce or salad greens.

title: corned beef sandwich spread
directions: Grind all and mix with salad dressing.

title: turkey crunch casserole(great for leftovers from a turkey dinner)
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Stir soup and mayo together. Toss with turkey mixture.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with chow mein noodles.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly all over.

title: sparkling mallow dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add wine and strawberries. Chill until partially set.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into individual dessert dishes.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Wash rice.
In covered pan, gently cook rice (with salt) in water for 45 minutes.
Brown ground beef; set aside.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Combine soy sauce, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Add rice, beef, onion, mushroom mix, water chestnuts and olives.
Add most of the almonds, reserving some for garnish.
Place in a lightly greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Add water if needed and season to taste.
Garnish with almonds and parsley, if desired.

title: "easy" homemade bread
directions: Place flour, sugar, salt, yeast and eggs in large bowl. Heat milk and oil until hot; pour milk and oil mixture over ingredients and mix. Add enough flour to make stiff dough, not sticky. Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead for 5 minutes. Shape in a ball. Place in a lightly greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down. Knead 5 more minutes. Separate the dough in half to make loaves. Put in greased loaf pans. Cover and let rise double. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set aside pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups liquid.
In microwave bowl, combine liquid, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and 1/3 cup soy sauce.
Microwave on High for 7 1/2 to 11 minutes or until mixture is thick and glossy, stirring twice with whisk.
Set aside.

title: lemon chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift into an 8 x 8-inch ungreased baking pan the flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Make 3 holes in the dry ingredients. Into 1 hole, put vanilla.
In another hole put vinegar and in third hole put vegetable oil.
Pour cold water over everything. Stir until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Immediately after removing from oven, place candy bar squares around on the surface.
When melted, spread around to frost the cake.
Cut and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until thick.

title: carrot fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 Bundt shape muffin pans, two 6-cup pans or one 12-cup Bundt pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Stir and cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter, vanilla and few grains of salt. Beat until well blended and spread into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: irish cream of potato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chicken broth and garlic.
Add onion and carrots.
Cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add evaporated milk, skim milk, potato flakes, pepper and parsley.
Mix well to combine.
Lower heat.
Continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4. Freezes well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add milk to banana pudding.
Mix, using mixer for 2 minutes. Fold in Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding in large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Enjoy!

title: pollo borracho(drunk mexican chicken)
directions: Heat oil in large Dutch oven or electric skillet.
Brown chicken and add all spices and bouillon.
Reduce heat to medium low and add remaining ingredients, chopping tomatoes as added with juice.
Cook, covered, about 30 minutes and then cook, uncovered, another 15 to 30 minutes until chicken is done and liquid is somewhat reduced.
Very good served with rice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix catsup and water.
Sprinkle meat with 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into meat and turn over.
Add remainder of flour, salt and pepper.
Pound this into meat.
Brown on both sides of meat.
Add other ingredients.
Cover tightly and cook slowly on top of stove for 1 hour.

title: zucchini mexicali
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Add zucchini, carrot, onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic salt, basil and pepper.
Toss to mix well.
Cook covered over medium heat 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine taco sauce and mustard; stir into vegetables.
Add tomato; cook uncovered for 3 to 5 minutes. Season with salt.
Sprinkle shredded sharp cheese or Mozzarella on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: unbelievable meatballs
directions: Make your favorite recipe for meatballs; do not brown. Combine spaghetti sauce and cranberry sauce.
Place in slow cooker or large saucepan.
Add the meatballs.
In a slow cooker, cook on low for 4 hours.
In a saucepan, cover and cook on low heat for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Then let cool.
Peel off skin and debone all the meat.
In a large pot combine Velveeta, sour cream, rotel, cumin and soup until cheese is melted.
Put in tortillas; chicken, monterey jack cheese and about 2 tablespoons of velveeta mix.
Roll up and lay in cake pan.
When done put left over chicken, velveeta sauce, and monterey jack cheese over the top of rolled enchiladas.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bean burrito bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix well refried beans, Bisquick and water.
Spread mixture in bottom and halfway up side of greased 10-inch deep pie plate.
Layer in order: hamburger, avocado, salsa and Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Each piece may be served with a dollop of sour cream.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix
pineapple and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil. Dissolve
gelatin
in cold water and add to pineapple mixture. Set aside
to
cool.
Crush cherries.
Add cherry juice to the cream cheese
and
mix
until smooth.
Add cherries and lemon juice. Combine
with gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar
and
margarine;
cut
cream
cheese into 3 parts. Add alternately with eggs, one at a time.	Add flavorings.
Sift flour and add to mixture 1 cup at a time.
Bake in a greased
and floured
tube
pan	at
300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Put all of the ingredients into a large mixing bowl. Everything can be added without sifting.
Beat for 20 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool cake on rack 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 20.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put Master Cake Mix in bowl; blend in additional sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well, then add sour cream and vanilla. This can be mixed with electric mixer or by hand.
Beat thoroughly until batter is smooth.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift flour; add sugar and salt.
In medium saucepan, bring to a boil the buttermilk, water and cocoa.
Add to flour mixture. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bananas supreme
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Peel bananas, brush with lemon juice, then dip in sugar mixture.
Wrap bacon strip around each banana; secure with wooden toothpicks.
Sprinkle apples with remaining sugar mixture.
Place fruit in broiler 4 inches from heat.
Broil 10 to 12 minutes; turn bananas once.
Remove from pan and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best baked beans
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet, stirring until it crumbles; drain well.
Return sausage to skillet; add onion and bell pepper and cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat; stir in pork and beans and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Yield: 5 3/4 cups.

title: sarma
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make into balls.
Roll into cabbage leaves that have been in salted boiling water 1 to 2 days.
Brown flour in ham or bacon fat.
Mix in 1 can tomato puree.
Simmer; add 1 can sauerkraut.
Mix well; then add meat balls.
Add another can sauerkraut and some water.
Cook slowly 3 to 3 1/2 hours, until tender.

title: easy tuna burgers
directions: Cut the onion and celery into rough quarters.
Place them in a food processor and pulsing the machine on and off, process until coarsely chopped.
Add the tuna and process briefly to break it up.
Add the egg, bread, butter, mustard, cayenne and black pepper and process until just blended.
Place the flour in a shallow bowl.
Lightly flour your hands and shape the tuna mixture into four patties, about 4-inches across.
Dredge the patties lightly in the flour.
In a large skillet, preferably nonstick, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add the patties and cook until browned, about 3 minutes on each side.
Serve them hot!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, Ranch dressing mix and cream cheese. Lay crescent rolls out flat on a cookie sheet or pizza pan and brown in oven.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of crust and then add any vegetables you like (i.e. carrots, celery, cauliflower, broccoli, bell peppers, green onions).
Top with shredded cheese and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo, cream cheese and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add other ingredients and
beat
well.
Bake
in 10-inch Bundt cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
