Use 6 dessert glasses (not dishes) and fill halfway with Cool Whip, then the other half with pudding.
Top with cherry on each glass.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 1/2 minutes after it boils.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on crackers or use for sandwiches.

title: zesty sausage squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix with milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise. Spread in well-greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pat down.
Saute sausage and onion.
Drain and spread on top of meat layer.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve for brunch or main dish supper.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple juice into small bowl.
Add cornstarch, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Set aside.
Combine beaten egg, flour, water and salt and pepper.
Dip pork pieces in it.
Brown pork pieces in small amount of oil.
Stir in onion and sauce. Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in pineapple chunks.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Serves 2.

title: parmesan hot bread
directions: Break loaf in half the long way.
Slice the rest into even slices.
Spread each slice with mayonnaise and top with onion slice and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Lay on cookie sheet and bake in 400° preheated oven for ten minutes or until the cheese is bubbly and lightly browned.

title: she crab soup(from charleston receipts)
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler and blend with flour until smooth.
Add milk gradually stirring constantly.
To this, add crabmeat and eggs and all seasonings except sherry.
Cook slowly over hot water for 20 minutes.
To serve place 1 tablespoon of warmed sherry in individual soup bowls, then add soup and top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with paprika or finely chopped parsley.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Dip breasts in milk, then dredge in seasoned crumbs, mixed with grated cheese.
Arrange chicken on well-greased baking dish. Put slice of butter on each chicken breast.
Bake 25 minutes at 450°.
Then remove from oven and put 2 tablespoons of heated sauce and 1 slice of Mozzarella on each breast.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple-chicken and rice bake
directions: Place chicken pieces, onion and red pepper into a large plastic bag set in a deep bowl.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together undrained pineapple, orange juice concentrate, soy sauce and cloves.
Pour pineapple mixture over chicken mixture in bag. Seal bag.
Marinate the mixture in the refrigerator for 4 to 24 hours. Turn bag occasionally.

title: orange glaze
directions: Combine all the ingredients together into medium saucepan and cook on low until thickened.
Spread on grilled pork chops.

title: holly sprigs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in flour, vanilla and nuts. Roll dough, a level teaspoon at a time into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Press down to 1-inch rounds.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden around edges.
When cool, put two cookies together with preserves.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.
Makes 3 dozen double cookies.

title: bagogi (korean)
directions: Marinate 24 hours.
Cook slowly until juices evaporate.
Serve cooked over rice.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in a 9-inch pie pan.
Add cocoa, sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.

title: hot artichoke dip(low fat recipe)
directions: Chop artichoke hearts in a food processor. Add parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, garlic clove, lemon zest, cayenne (to taste); puree until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Place in a 2 cup baking dish (this dish can be prepared to this point and refrigerated up to 2 days ahead). Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. Parmesan. Bake at 400° until top is golden and dip is heated through, 10 to 20 minutes.

title: cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to directions, drain.
In medium skillet, cook and stir beef until browned. Remove from heat, drain. Stir in sauce, soup, pepper and seasoning.
In greased 4 qt baking dish, combine pasta, sauce mix and 2 cups of cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cup of cheese on top. Bake 40 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone, cut or cube and put in casserole dish. Cook broccoli, drain and place over chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix and let it sit overnight.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Butter Bundt pan and flour lightly.
Combine all ingredients; beat 5 minutes.
In preheated 350° oven bake 50 minutes to 1 hour. Check with toothpick until comes out clean!
Cool in pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all except consomme.
Form into balls (golf ball size). Pour two 10 ounce cans of beef consomme over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Pour off liquid, spoon off grease and use a package of brown gravy mix to make gravy.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Crush 2 ounces corn chips; line bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch). Brown ground beef and onion; drain grease.
Combine tomato sauce, taco seasoning and beans with meat.
Put meat mixture in pan on top of chips.
Top with rest of chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: two pineapple pies
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch, dash of salt and pineapple. Beat this mixture, then add milk and margarine.
Cook until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
Add dash of salt and 2 tablespoons sugar; put on pies and brown.

title: harvest vegetable casserole
directions: Wash and cook vegetables until tender.
Drain.
Cut vegetables into bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
In separate container, mix together crushed crackers and melted oleo.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mom's filled cookies
directions: Mix in order given; roll thin.
Put one cookie on ungreased sheet.
Put about 1 teaspoon filling.
Place another cookie on top and pinch together.
Prick holes with a fork on top of filling. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, cream cheese and sour cream in bowl; mix well.
Stir in shrimp.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Yield:
80 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream oleo and cream cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Gradually blend with dry cake mix, mixing well. Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator and form dough into small balls.
Roll balls in ground nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
If desired, press a cherry half into each ball.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: great hot dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Cook well and then drain very well! Return sausage to skillet and add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until all is well blended.
Serve warm with corn chips or snack crackers.

title: sugar-free, fat-free lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all of these ingredients with the aid of a mixer. Then fold in 1/2 tub of Cool Whip (lite). Mix well. Pour into a graham cracker pie crust. Chill.

title: chicken hot dish(serves 6)
directions: Cook and debone chicken and place in casserole dish.
Melt cheese and mix with soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Moisten croutons with chicken broth and butter and toss.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use 6 x 8-inch or 8 x 11-inch pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Bring 1 1/2 cups sugar, peaches and margarine to a boil; cook shortly.
Pour peach mixture into square baking dish.
Pour first mixture all over top of peach mixture.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon and cream cheese and spread in the crust. Keep in refrigerator.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Brown meat slowly, add onion and pepper and continue browning. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 1/2 hour.
Stir now and then.

title: six-in-one casserole
directions: Arrange in layers as given in the ingredients.
Slice the potatoes and spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover potatoes with onion.
Crumble beef over onion.
Cover beef with the tomatoes and cover top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: apricot buttons
directions: Combine apricots and 1/3 cup sugar; cook until thickened. Cool.
Cream butter and remaining 1/3 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Chill dough slightly.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Trim leaves from broccoli.
Split stems and soak in cold salted water for 1 hour.
Drain.
Reserve 8 florets for garnish. Steam broccoli until tender; reserve liquid.
Process broccoli in food processor.
Set aside.
Saute onions in butter until tender; whisk in flour.
Gradually whisk in milk, one cup at a time. Whisk in pureed broccoli.
When hot, add cheese and whisk until melted.
Add broccoli cooking water to thin as desired.
Add salt. Garnish with florets.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream just until mixed well.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, then remainder of ingredients (except pecans). Place in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Spread pecans on waxed paper. With wet hands, shape two cheese balls.
Roll in nuts. Refrigerate until used. Can be frozen.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients together and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake in baking dish.
Drain off all juice.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's chocolate dumplings
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring the first ingredients to a boil. Add butter.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix crackers, butter and poppy seed together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
(Save one cup for topping.)
Parboil chicken with salt, black pepper, onions and celery.
Place chopped up chicken over cracker crust.
Cream sour cream, cream of chicken soup; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cracker mixture on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and form into a ball. Roll in crushed nuts.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Blend in egg.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: cream cheese crescent cake
directions: Press 1 roll of crescent rolls into 9 x 13 pan. Mix cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice. Spread over layer of rolls. Press other package of rolls over cream cheese mixture. Beat egg white and coat top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: smothered okra(serves 4)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender (about 5 minutes). Stir in okra, tomatoes, salt and peppers. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: gingerbread
directions: Bake in moderate oven, about 25 minutes.
Check with toothpick.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine butter, sugar and brown sugar; beat until creamy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla extract; beat well.
Gradually blend in flour.
Stir in oats, 1/2 cup nuts and coconut.
Spread into lightly greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Grate cheese and mix with softened margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill, roll into marble size balls.
Press with fork, glass or finger to make wafer.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 5 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mold together with hands into ball and roll in pecans.
Serve on crackers.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with 1 crust.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, and salt.
Stir into rhubarb.
Pour into pie pan.
Dot with butter and sprinkle lemon juice all over.
Bake 40-50 minutes at 375.

title: grammy's blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add egg, stirring well.
Mix together flour, baking powder, and salt and add alternately with buttermilk.
Shake 1 tablespoon flour over the blueberries and add to the mixture.
Bake in greased or paper lined muffin cups at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries and oranges. Put through food chopper. Mix together and add sugar. Put in jar and refrigerate. Keeps about 3 weeks.

title: hearty chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart shallow baking dish, mix soups, milk, pepper, thyme, vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Stir.
Arrange biscuits over chicken mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
Serves 5.
Prep Time:
15 minutes. Cook Time:
30 minutes.

title: confetti sundae
directions: Drain cocktail; stir in flavoring.
Chill.
Cut 2 1/2-inch circle from center of doily.
Lay onto edge of wide top custard cup.
Place scoop of ice cream in cup; surround with cocktail and top with whipped cream.

title: low sodium-cream soup mix
directions: Mix together. Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix first 6 items. Divide in half.
Spread first half in 2-quart Pyrex pan and congeal. Spread sour cream as second layer. Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Pour remaining jello mix on top of sour cream. Congeal.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: orange muffins
directions: Mix orange juice and rind, lemon juice and sugar.
Set; stand in refrigerator overnight.
Make cake batter; pour in mini-muffin tins and bake.
While hot, dip in juice mixture and drain on wire rack.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Freezes well.

title: "berry" crunch
directions: Spread berries evenly in 2 quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over berries.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Peel, core and slice apples; set aside in large bowl.
Blend oil, eggs and sugar with mixer; add baking powder and flours. Blend until combined.
Pour batter over apples and gently mix until slices are well coated.
Pour mixture of apples and batter into the baking pan; apple slices should be spread out evenly. Bake until knife comes out clean, 35 to 45 minutes.
Great for after school with a glass of milk, or serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into large mixer bowl; beat until well mashed. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan at least 15 minutes. Remove from the pan; finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Cake can be baked in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt, stirring well.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans and coconut.
Pour filling into shell; top with remaining pecans.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: mother's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine eggs, onion, soup and mayonnaise.
Layer broccoli in a 2 quart baking dish.
Add layers of cheese and sauce.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mr. ed's baked fish
directions: Using a greased Corning Ware loaf pan, make one layer of fish fillets and sprinkle with parsley, onions, salt, pepper, pieces of margarine and lemon juice.
Repeat 3 times.
On final layer, sprinkle 3 to 4 tablespoons of lemon juice.
Cover with 1/4-inch of real mayonnaise.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Melt margarine and add celery, onion and chicken broth. Simmer until tender.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients; fold in next 3 ingredients.
Bake in three 8-inch pans until done at 350°. Blend together next 5 ingredients with juice of strawberries until proper spreading consistency.
Spread on cakes.
Stack.

title: fresh basil-tomato spaghetti
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Heat saute pan over medium-high heat; add oil and garlic.
Saute but do not brown.
Add fresh and sundried tomatoes to pan.
Add wine and chicken broth to deglaze; add 1/2 the basil.
Heat together until liquid is reduced by 1/2.
Add butter, melt and remove from heat. Toast pine nuts at 350° for 5 minutes.
Toss pasta with sauce, top with Parmesan, remaining basil and pine nuts.
Serves 2.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until plump (about 15 minutes).
Drain and keep liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 1/2 cup. Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid. Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and oats.
Add nuts. Drop about 2-inches on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy salad
directions: Place candy and 1 cup water in saucepan and bring to a boil. Stir until candy is dissolved.
Add 2 cups water and dash of salt. Pour over gelatin in a bowl and stir until gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into mold.
Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: beef roast
directions: Wash the roast good under cool, running water.
Place in a large deep Corning dish.
Add onion for seasoning, garlic powder and other vegetables, as you prefer.
Add about an inch of water to dish.
Heat on a burner.
Have oven hot, ready to cook roast, for about 1 1/2 hours.
Put foil over the top of the roaster and place lid on.
Place in hot oven; continue cooking until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after
each
egg.
Add
vanilla and flour, a little at a time. Beat
well,
but
don't overbeat.
Cook in slow oven at 350°
for 1 hour.
Pour mixture in ungreased pan or angel food cake pan.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter, powdered sugar and Rice Krispies. Form in balls and put in refrigerator while preparing dip.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan at 350°.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix soups together; add 1 teaspoon each garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Saute onions in butter. Add 1/2 cup cooked rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
I like to put about 1 cup of grated cheese in mine.
Bake until bubbly hot at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put ingredients in large baking dish in order listed, putting parsley and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered, and an additional 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: shipwreck
directions: Spray large baking dish with Pam or other cooking spray. Layer potatoes with small dabs of margarine.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over potatoes and onion over rice.
Next, cover with chunks of uncooked hamburger.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Pour stewed tomatoes over the top.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add glaze.

title: swedish angel lemon pie
directions: Beat the egg whites until frothy, then add cream of tartar. Beat until stiff and then gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Spread in a buttered 9-inch pie pan and bake at 300° for about 25 minutes or until meringue is set and slightly brown.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Cook in double boiler, stirring until thickened.
(If after cooking the filling becomes too thick, add 2 tablespoons hot water.)
When meringue and filling are cool, whip the cream.
Blend half of the whipped cream with the filling and spread over meringue.
Spread with remaining whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: mini cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottoms of each of 12 paper or foil-lined muffin cups with spoon. Beat milk and filling mix on low until blended.
Beat on medium 3 minutes.
Filling will be thick.
Spoon over crumb mixture in muffin cups.
Garnish.
Refrigerate.

title: quickie cheese bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters; place in a loaf pan.
Sprinkle cheese throughout.
Beat egg and pour over biscuits.
Pour melted butter over all.
Sprinkle with garlic and chopped chives.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan (pulls apart).

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix and 2 eggs and pat into pan.
Blend softened cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, cucumber, peanuts and onion in a large bowl.
Set mixture aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix
well.	Add
to
cabbage mixture;
toss well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts. Pour in ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: yogurt chicken breasts(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and yogurt, in a shallow dish and mix well.
Brush chicken pieces with yogurt and roll chicken in crumb mixture.
Place in a greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Drizzle with some melted margarine and sprinkle on some sesame seed.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until browned and done. Serve with Creamy Yogurt Sauce.

title: blue cheese potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes and prepare as for cooking.
Tear foil paper to hold one serving for as many servings as needed.
Put potatoes in foil.
Add salt, pepper, margarine and Blue cheese to each pack. Seal tightly and bake about 30 minutes or until done.
Makes a good alternative with steak instead of baked potatoes.

title: hot red skin potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken-ham roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breasts very flat. Place slice of ham and slice of cheese on each flattened chicken breast.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Brown rolls in frying pan with a little butter or Pam spray.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix together the soup and wine (or water).
Cover the chicken rolls with this mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together and pour over the cereal.
Mix.
Pour the confectioners sugar in a paper bag and add cereal mixture. Shake to coat.
Spread on wax paper to dry.
Good for kids!

title: bambinos or baby pizza
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread crackers on cookie sheet.
Spoon sauce or catsup on cracker; top with pepperoni.
Sprinkle with cheese and oregano.
Bake just until cheese melts, 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: s'mores
directions: Find a nice secluded beach.
Wait until the evening, then build a big bonfire.
Roast marshmallows over the bonfire until golden brown.
Place 2 squares chocolate on half of a graham cracker.
Add roasted marshmallow.
Top with other half of graham cracker to form a sandwich; eat and enjoy!

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water, then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Beat well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes
in
three 9 inch pans.
Cool.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the margarine, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Add cocoa and milk.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Fold into creamed mixture with walnuts and chocolate chips.
Roll teaspoons of dough into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing to wire racks.
Yield: 3 to 4 dozen.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in oil.
Drain excess fat. Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in brown sugar and chili sauce. Bring just to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve on sandwich buns.

title: marinated spaghetti salad
directions: Bring 2 quarts of water to a boil and cook 1 pound of spaghetti noodles until slightly tender.
Drain; rinse noodles with cool water and refrigerate.
Whisk together the Italian dressing with all the spices until well blended.
Cut the cucumbers and red onions and add to the marinade, then fold in the cooked noodles.
Refrigerate this overnight in a covered container.
Before serving, garnish with fresh parsley sprigs and diced tomatoes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine soup, rice and water; mix well in casserole dish. Place chicken on top of mixture.
Season chicken with pepper and seasoned salt.
Cut up oleo and place on top of chicken.
Cook uncovered about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Dot with butter and Thousand Island dressing.
Cover with corned beef.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven.
Split biscuits in half and place on top of cheese.
Sprinkle with crushed Rye Krisps and caraway seed. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, until topping is brown.
Serves about 6 people.

title: pasta bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook the mushrooms, onion and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta.
Return to boil.
Cook for 12 minutes or until pasta is al dente.
Stir in undrained tomatoes and garbanzo beans.
Heat through.
Just before serving, stir in fresh basil and thyme.
Makes 4 servings.

title: southwestern spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to pkg. directions. In large skillet cook beef and onions until done and drain. Stir in taco seasoning, spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and olives. Drain spaghetti and stir into beef mixture.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cheese with fork, add clams and enough juice for desired consistency.
Add seasoning and chill overnight.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add enough milk to make a roll.
Roll or pat on floured counter; cut with circle cutter or glass.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: horseradish roast
directions: Brown roast unfloured.
Add salt, pepper, sliced onions, horseradish and red wine.
Bake at 325° for 4 to 5 hours in covered roasting pan.
Serves 6.

title: beef or pork sauce
directions: Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over uncooked meat and let set (as little as 30 minutes or as long as all day). Use remaining sauce with meat after it's cooked!
I recommend using this sauce with pork tenderloin.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Remove flavor packets from Ramen noodles. Crush noodles and place with almonds on cookie sheet. Spray lightly with cooking spray and broil until lightly brown. Combine slaw mix, noodles and almonds. Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and flavor packets from noodles together. Pour dressing over slaw before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together, adding ginger ale and lime sherbet just before serving.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Lay patty on sheet of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle garlic powder to taste.
Add potatoes, onions and peppers.
Add margarine last. Seal foil over top.
Place on cookie tray.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: dolmathes(stuffed grape leaves)
directions: Mix meat and egg(s).
Add onions, parsley, mint, oregano, garlic, olive oil, rice and 1/4 cup water.
Season with salt and pepper.
If using fresh grape leaves, soak in hot water 5 minutes to soften.
If using canned/bottled grape leaves, rinse in warm water.
Place spoonful of meat mixture on leaf (shiny side down) and roll, folding ends as you go to seal.
Line large cooking pot with a layer of plain leaves.
Layer dolmathes neatly in pot, add broth and enough water to cover.
Place a heavy pot on top inside the pot to keep dolmathes in place.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: omelet
directions: Beat eggs, add flour and water.
Beat again.
Pour into hot, greased skillet.
Cook on medium temperature.
When partially set, add pepperoni and cheese.
Turn and cook until brown.

title: japanese spareribs with pineapple
directions: Have butcher cut ribs into 1-inch lengths.
Mix with flour, soy and red soy.
Heat 1 tablespoon peanut oil in pan and add garlic and ginger.
Brown ribs.
Add vinegar, water, salt and sugar. Allow to cook over low flame for an hour.
Garnish with pineapple, cut into small pieces.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli according to package directions; drain. Combine with corn, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, onion flakes, 2 tablespoons margarine, salt and pepper in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon margarine in small bowl.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: beef stew
directions: *Jarred onions may be used.

title: apple delight
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Pour apple mixture into dish.
Sprinkle oatmeal mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: original tea cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is "mealy."
Beat eggs and vanilla. Knead until dough is soft enough to roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Mash flat.
Bake at 375° until cookies start to brown.
The secret is not to overcook these.

title: chewy coconut cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Add sugars gradually, beating thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing until blended.
Mix in coconut, vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° until cookies just begin to brown.

title: esta's cheese straws
directions: Mix soft cheese and margarine.
Add red pepper.
Add flour, one cup at a time until the dough begins to pull away from the bowl. (Add flour until it pulls away but is still soft.)
Shape into balls (size of a quarter) and place a pecan half on top.
Bake at 350° (preheated) for about 20 minutes until crisp.
If you have a pastry press, use the piece that will make straws or flat sticks.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight. Drain and put all ingredients in slow cooker. Add 1 cup water and stir to blend. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours. Can also spice it up with a few cloves of garlic, 1/2 tsp powdered ginger and a good dash of Worcestershire sauce.

title: onion soup - french style
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add cut up onions and brown, stirring constantly.
Add flour; stir until flour is brown, also.
Gradually add water until well blended.
Let cook on low about 5 minutes.
While soup is cooking, place thick slices of French bread in soup bowls.
Top with grated cheese and pour soup over it.

title: apple pie in a sack
directions: Shake sugar, spice, flour and apples in a sack.
Arrange in a pie crust.
Combine butter, brown sugar, flour and pinch of salt to make crumb topping.
Sprinkle on apple mixture.
Bake in a sealed brown paper sack (do not use recycled sack) for 1 hour. Bake at 425°.

title: company carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots into diagonal slices.
Place in a 2 qt. pan with orange juice, olive oil, salt and sugar.
Add a dash of ginger.
Cover and heat to boiling, then reduce heat to medium low.
Cook until tender- about 35 minutes.
Add grapes.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: mock country ham
directions: Pat sugar generously and firmly over ham slice.
Gently pour 7-Up over sugar and ham and into the pan.
Bake in 350° oven; baste with sugar and 7-Up from bottom of pan often.
Tastes like real country ham.

title: classic chicken
directions: In one bowl, mix sour cream, sauce, lemon juice and garlic powder.
In second bowl, mix stuffing ingredients.
Coat chicken breast in sour cream.
Mix and then roll in bread stuffing.
Put in casserole dish.
Lay chicken side by side.
Pour melted butter evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes; reserve skins.
In medium saucepan over high heat, heat grape pulp to boiling, stirring occasionally; reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes, stirring.
Press pulp through sieve into medium bowl to remove seeds.
Add grape skins, sugar, tapioca and lemon juice; mix well.
Let stand while preparing pastry.

title: royal seafood casserole(may be prepared ahead of time.)
directions: In a large bowl, blend soup into mayo until smooth.
Add onion, then milk.
Season heavily because rice is bland and so is seafood. When well seasoned, combine with other ingredients except paprika and almonds.
Check seasonings; add a few tablespoons milk if mixture seems dry.
It should be moist.
Turn into a large shallow buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Scatter almonds generously over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Freezes well.
Serves 10.

title: trey's easy coconut cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions in 9x13-inch baking pan.
Let cake cool for 5 minutes.
Mix cream of coconut & sweetened condensed milk together.
Pour over cake.
Let cake cool completely.
Use cool whip for icing.
Sprinkle with as much coconut as desired.

title: sponge whip cake
directions: Early in the day, in large bowl, blend eggs, sugar, milk, salt and lemon juice.
Then, with mixer at high speed, beat until mixture holds soft peaks, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Start heating oven at 350°.
Using low speed, gradually beat flour into egg mixture, then pour batter into 10-inch tube pan which has been rinsed with cold water.
Bake 45 minutes or until surface springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Turn cake pan upside-down over neck of bottle and cool cake, then remove it from pan.
Place on cake stand; sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
Garnish with whole berries.
Or serve with a fresh or frozen fruit or with canned fruit:
perhaps, three small cans of different fruits, served as one, with some of the juice.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in glass jar. Use approximately 1 heaping teaspoonful per cup. Add hot water just like instant coffee.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, put pudding, milk and orange juice.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Blend into fruit.
Cover and chill.

title: peanut butter jack-o-lanterns
directions: Note:
Butter should be at room temperature.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Carefully remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix together eggs, mayonnaise, seafood seasoning, white pepper, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Add crabmeat; mix evenly and gently.
Add cracker crumbs evenly.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Deep fry in oil at 350° for 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown or saute in a frying pan with a little oil for 5 minutes on each side.

title: clara's zucchini bread
directions: Slice
walnuts;
shred zucchini to get 1 1/2 cups full. Blend in bowl.
Add oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder, blend 15 seconds.
Add flour.
Stir in nuts and zucchini by hand into mixture.
Use a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: chicken baked in beer
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces; cook and drain.
Brown chicken in bacon grease and set aside.
Brown onions.
Drain excess fat.
Mix dry ingredients and add to pan.
Slowly stir in flour, followed by beer and vinegar.
Cook on High for 5 minutes, until thickened. Return chicken to Pyrex dish.
Pour onions and bacon over top; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream together sour cream and cream cheese.
Add the drained green chilies, chopped jalapenos and peanuts.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up and chill.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix grated potatoes, milk, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Blend first and second mixtures. Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours to 1 3/4 hours.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: raw veggie dip
directions: Mix together and enjoy.

title: white fruit cake(makes 5 pound cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs. Use rotary beater; blend well.
Chop nuts and fruits in medium size pieces.
Mix with part of flour.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together.
Fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add flavoring.
Mix well.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and paper-lined tube pan.
Place into cold oven.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
Just as good second day after baked as it is 3 months after baking.
It can be stored in the refrigerator a year or can be frozen indefinitely.
May be baked in 2 loaf pans for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: cheesy beans
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Put in pan.
Add water and salt.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours or until soft.
Add more water if necessary while cooking.
Chop onion.
Put in large skillet with butter.
Add beans and mash with fork.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serve.

title: aunt phyllis' baked chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, soup, water and rice.
Place in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Put chow mein noodles on top and bake 15 minutes more. (Cornflakes or Special K may be used as the topping.)

title: easter salad
directions: Mix all together; chill and serve.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: Turkey:
Thaw turkey.
Rub with salt.
Unwrap liver and gizzard; place back inside turkey to bake.
Dip a white cloth in cup of melted oleo; wrap around turkey.
Cover with heavy wide foil.
Place in roaster on a rack.
Keep about 1-inch of water in bottom.
Bake according to instructions with turkey.
Remove foil and cloth, saving broth from inside foil and add 2 cans chicken broth and 4 bouillon cubes.
Set broth aside for dressing and giblet gravy.
Remove bone from turkey and arrange meat on platter.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside. Cream sugar with butter.
Add egg, orange rind and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
(Add nuts and raisins for a more traditional flavor. Our family prefers them with chocolate chips!)
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave p'nut brittle
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave 4 minutes and stir.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes more. Stir in margarine and vanilla; microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet and cool for 30 minutes.
Break and eat or store.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins., Spread evenly into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 24 bars.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, flour and cashews.
Press in bottom of baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Bake until light brown, about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: golden pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt well by hand.
Add egg white, water and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly until you can knead it in your mixing pan.
This will make 3 single crusts and will keep in refrigerator.
Wrap in plastic wrap, then aluminum foil.
Pinch off enough for 1
pie shell.
Rewrap until needed.

title: english toffee squares
directions: Sprinkle nuts over bottom of buttered 8-inch square dish.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, place brown sugar, butter and water. Microwave on 100% power 5 to 6 minutes, until thick.
Stir once during cooking.
Quickly spread mixture over chopped nuts. Sprinkle chocolate bits.
Cover dish so heat melts chocolate. Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly over top. Refrigerate to set.
Turn out of dish and break into pieces to serve.
Yields 1 pound.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt chocolate bar and mix in 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Take the remaining cup of peanut butter and melt in a Pyrex cup set in water in a pot.
Use paper muffin cups.
Put 1 tablespoon of chocolate first and let it set.
Then, add 1 tablespoon of peanut butter and let it set.
Cover with chocolate.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While cake is hot, put on marshmallow cream.
Add rest of frosting.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: clam fritters
directions: Place the clams and juice in blender or food processor.
Blend clams until just minced (they should not be pureed).
Pour minced clams into bowl; add pepper, evaporated milk, pancake mix and egg. Mix well.
Heat frying pan to 375° and grease lightly.
For each fritter, scoop out 1 tablespoon of mixture into hot pan.
When brown, turn and brown other side.
Keep greasing pan as needed.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spray baking dish with oil.
Place apples and water in pan. Combine remaining ingredients and place on top of the apples. Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: slaw by nathaniel
directions: Cut cabbage head into large bowl.
Cut onion and pepper on top.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle sugar over mixture.
Boil remaining ingredients and pour over mixture.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and 2 sticks of butter.
Press into 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Combine sugar, eggs, vanilla and 2 sticks of butter; beat for 10 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Press bananas, cut lengthwise, into the pudding.
Pour the drained pineapple on top of bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Arrange cherries and walnuts on top and chill at least 4 hours.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine juice and rind with egg.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spoon in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna salad hawaiian
directions: Mix tuna, pineapple, celery and walnuts.
Mix together mayonnaise, curry powder and parsley.
Add to tuna and chill. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together; beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add milk and melted shortening.
Pour slowly into dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake in hot waffle iron or skillet.
Makes 6 waffles.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in half length wise then slice as thin as possible.
Add
all ingredients and cook in the oven at 375° in a casserole dish or in a heavy boiler on stove top.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: greek chicken
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with lemon juice, then the garlic, oregano and pepper. Let marinate 10 minutes. Place the chicken in a baking dish that has been coated with the cooking spray. Bake at 350, 15-20 minutes until well done and lightly brown. Do not overcook.

title: west virginia fried chicken
directions: Mix all together. Coat chicken in mixture and fry in butter and oil.

title: candy date loaf
directions: Cook sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball in water.
Add chopped dates and beat until thick.
Add pecans and/or coconut. Have a tea towel, which has been soaked in cold water.
Wring out. Spread mixture on towel, then roll mixture in towel into approximately 1-inch rope.
When cool, slice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar. Add eggs one at a time until fluffy. Add 1 cup of flour and then a small amount of 7-UP. Add 1 cup flour and then some more 7-UP. Repeat again. Mix well. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add grated sweet potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Dot butter on top.
Bake in moderate oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: peach-cranberry yam bake
directions: In large bowl, combine yams and peaches.
Blend cranberry sauce with reserved syrup from yams.
Drizzle over yams and peaches.
Add nuts; gently toss to mix well.
Spoon mixture evenly into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or microwave uncovered on High for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana-wheat quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch pan.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Immediately remove from pan; cool.
Make 4 miniature loaves using 5 x 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pans or soup cans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Make pudding by directions and add whipped cream.
Stir until consistent.
Place 1 layer of cookies in bottom of serving dish, layer with pudding mixture, then bananas.
Do 3 layers and cool in refrigerator 6 hours.

title: mermaid delights(tuna burgers)
directions: Split and butter buns.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except for hamburger buns.
Fill the buns with tuna mixture.
Wrap each bun in a square of foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with usual condiments for hamburgers, ketchup, mustard, relish, etc.
Serves 6.

title: do ahead dried beef casserole
directions: Stir soup with onion, cheese, macaroni and beef.
Fold in eggs.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: man's favorite salad
directions: Shred the cabbage and onion very fine.
Mix mayonnaise and cottage cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste. Toss and refrigerate.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Arrange onion rings on top and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Place in unbaked pie shell.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in a greased, oven safe dish.

title: frozen pie filling(store in freezer)
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup milk to soften.
Scald rest of milk over medium heat.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in 3-quart saucepan.
Gradually add scalded milk.
Cook over medium heat and stir constantly, about 10 minutes until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir some of mixture into egg yolks and pour back into pan.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and mix in gelatin, margarine and vanilla.
Put in foil-lined pie pans.
Freeze.
Remove from pan when frozen and prepare to store.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Rub the surface of the roast with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter or margarine on all sides.
Add the water, tomato juice, chopped onions and sliced garlic.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Add to the meat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: famous jam cake
directions: Coat pecans and raisins with flour.
Mix all together and bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: million dollar torte
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 12 minutes.
Beat cream cheese at high speed; add 2 cups milk gradually at low speed.
Sprinkle in instant vanilla pudding mix and beat until thick.
Spread on cold cake. Drain pineapple and spread on pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours overnight.
Torte can be frozen for months.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mash potatoes with salt, milk and butter.
Combine tomato juice, salt, peppers, egg, bread crumbs, onions and mustard.
Add ground beef or turkey and mix well.
Put mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press in well.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Drain off grease.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Bake additional 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large pan and cook to soft ball stage.
Scrape from bottom frequently.
(It will be dark brown in color.)
Beat in pan for few minutes and add nuts and vanilla. Beat until you can drop on wax paper.
If it seems to be getting hard too fast, put the pan in another pan of hot water.

title: olive surprises
directions: Have butter and cheese at room temperature.
Blend them together with fingertips.
Add flour gradually, blend in well. Add garlic salt and Tabasco and mix well.
Break off small bits and flatten in palm of hand, using just enough to wrap completely around an olive.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
If pie crust edges start to burn, cover with foil until filling is done.
Cool.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put half of bread in dish. Cover with all of the cream cheese and bacon.
Place remaining bread on top.
Beat the eggs. Add the milk and maple syrup.
Pour over bread mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Place in preheated oven and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: favorite stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, blend cornstarch into soy sauce; stir in orange juice; set aside.
Preheat skillet over high heat.
Add cooking oil.
Stir-fry lean meat or fish until almost cooked.
Add vegetables.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in cornstarch mixture; add in fruit.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: veal bundles
directions: Heat 1 teaspoon oil in large pan at medium heat.
Add garlic (saute 30 seconds).
Add mushrooms (saute 3 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley, raisins, bread crumbs and Parmesan.
Lay scaloppine flat.
Spread about 1/3 cup stuffing over each scaloppine.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Wipe skillet. Saute rolls in remaining oil in skillet for 5 minutes until brown. Add broth and carrot and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove rolls to plate (keep warm).
Remove picks.
Stir tomatoes into skillet. Boil rapidly 5 minutes until slightly thickened.
Add rolls. Heat through.

title: sweet pepper chicken saute
directions: Cut chicken into strips of equal size (may be flattened if necessary).
Sprinkle with Creole seasoning; set aside for 15 to 30 minutes.
Saute chicken quickly in margarine for approximately 5 to 10 minutes in fairly hot skillet.
Add pepper strips; stir-fry over high heat until tender-crisp.
Quickly add soy sauce.
Serve with rice or noodles, cooked in chicken broth. Serves 2 to 4.

title: lazy day beef stew
directions: Layer all ingredients except sour cream.
Cover.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours (300° for 2 1/2 hours).
Remove from oven and stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: breakfast casserole(sausage bake)
directions: Place croutons in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Cover with cheese, then sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard separately, then pour over cheese and sausage.
Let it stand overnight or all day in the refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve while hot!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together until smooth.
Add well beaten eggs, flour, salt, syrup, milk and flavoring and mix well. Add nuts and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: skillet burgers
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and celery until beef is brown and onion is tender; drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, quick cooking rolled oats, salt, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer uncovered until mixture is of desired consistency, about 30 minutes.
Spoon about 1/4 cup meat mixture into each bun.
Makes 14 to 16 sandwiches.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut biscuits into fourths and place in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Melt margarine and brown sugar together.
Stir and pour over biscuits.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Unmold.

title: swiss chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake shell 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 350°.

title: chocolate marble cheesecake
directions: Combine and press mixture onto bottom and sides of 9 inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: gas grill pizza
directions: In small bowl, mix together tomato sauce, basil, sugar, oregano and garlic powder.
Grease heavy skillet (iron skillet) and spread bread dough in bottom and slightly up the sides. Sprinkle with cooked meat and mushrooms.
Spread tomato sauce mixture over the top.
Sprinkle 2 cups (8 ounces) shredded Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at medium-high heat until golden brown, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.
Let pizza set 10 minutes.
Sliced olives may be added to pizza the last 15 minutes of cooking, if desired.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in a covered container.
Put 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in cup and pour in boiling water.

title: tomato pie
directions: Brown pie shell 10-15 minutes.
Put tomatoes, onions and crumbled bacon in shell.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese and spread over pie.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: yu shan eggplant
directions: Steam eggplant slices until tender (50 minutes in a steamer or 8 minutes in microwave). Chop and measure other ingredients and set aside.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cheese and eggs should be room temperature. Flour should be sifted. Cream together butter and cream cheese. Add sugar and cream. Add eggs 1 at a time. Mix in flour about half cup at a time. Add vanilla flavoring and mix. Grease and flour Bundt cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: oatmeal graham cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, cream together the butter or margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, flour, salt, soda, oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Store tightly covered.

title: peanut butter snaps
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and the rest of ingredients.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Shape in balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, pepper and parsley in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, mint, wine, rice, salt, Louisiana hot sauce and sausage, cover 1/2 to 3/4-inch with water.
Cover, simmer until water is almost all absorbed.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
In baking dish mix vegetables, soup and meat.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with Tater Tots and brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Form into a loaf.
Make 3 indentions.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the first 2 ingredients together for 3 minutes and cool. Cream the eggs, margarine and vanilla and add to raisin mixture. Add remaining ingredients to mixture and mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Time depends on size of cookie.

title: praline planks
directions: Line cookie sheet (foil-lined or with Pam) with crackers.
In saucepan, boil butter and sugar 3 minutes.
Quickly pour over crackers and spread.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool slightly.
Remove and separate onto wire racks until thoroughly cooled.
Store in airtight container.
Serves 4 1/2 dozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in following order:
oil, sugar, eggs, flour, salt, spices,
apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in cake pans and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: salad dressing to share
directions: Put all ingredients in a gallon jug and shake well.
Improves with age and may be shared with a friend.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with water and drain.
Cover with fresh water again and bring to a boil.
Drain again and mix sauerkraut with chopped vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Boil together 1 cup of water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper; pour hot liquid over all. Refrigerate immediately.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: granny's christmas cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
In another large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Put grated apples, chopped cherries and cherry juice together in a bowl.
Add dry ingredients and apple-cherry mixture alternately, in small amounts, to butter mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla. Pour into large greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check after an hour.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Do toothpick test.
If pick comes out clean, it's done.)

title: fudge brownies
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat lightly by hand just until combined.
Stir in flour and 1/2 cup nuts.

title: canned blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and buttermilk/soda mix.
Blend spices, cocoa and flour and add slowly to mixture.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Then add jam.
Take 1 cup flour and coat nuts and raisins.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Sift all other dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture with flour and buttermilk.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake in 3 (9 or 10-inch) pans.
Use your favorite icing.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: *If using sour apples, use 7 tablespoons sugar.

title: our favorite stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off top of peppers and scoop out seeds.
Mix ground beef, slightly cooked rice, chopped onion, salt, pepper, milk and catsup. If your pan is tall, stand up peppers and fill.
(You need a pan with a cover.)
Cook in electric skillet or bake in oven until 1/2 done.
If pan is shallow, cut peppers lengthwise and place on top of rice and ground beef mixture.
Mix undiluted soup with electric mixer.
Pour over peppers and simmer until peppers are thoroughly cooked.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well greased 13 x 9 x 1-inch iron frying skillet.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Ovens vary.

title: layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish spread cut-up lettuce.
Cook peas very briefly (about 2 minutes after they come to a boil).
Drain and cool in cold water.
Drain when cool and sprinkle over lettuce. Mix Miracle Whip and sugar; spread over peas.
Sprinkle on chopped onion and chopped pepper or these may be omitted.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Sprinkle on bacon or bits.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Arrange in covered dish in layers, beginning and ending with onions.
Add pimento for color if desired.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Grease and flour 12 medium muffin cups. Beat milk, oil and egg slightly.
Beat in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 425° until golden brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dorlyn's black bean soup
directions: Use either 1 pound of dried black beans (sometimes called turtle beans) or 4 cans black beans.
If you choose dried beans, soak them according to package and don't drain any remaining soaking water before proceeding with recipe.
Set beans aside.

title: walnut chews
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and egg with mixer until crumbly. Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and return to oven for 1 to 2 minutes more.
Let cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cook at 375 degrees in large pan, sprayed with pam until golden brown-will be moist when done.
I use a large cast iron fry pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam onion and zucchini 5 minutes.
Melt margarine.
Mix with stuffing mix.
Add milk and undiluted soup to zucchini and onion. Put half of stuffing in a baking dish.
Add zucchini and layer remaining dressing on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: very berry yogurt trifle
directions: If you love convenience and hate extra fats in your goodies, then you'll savor that love/hate relationship with this surprise ingredient.
The recipe is shorter than this sales pitch.
Prune puree, the expensive kind in a can, has been used to substitute for the high calorie oil used by some of us.
I adapted the idea slightly.
You might have a little smile on your face when you serve this cake or cupcake to amazed friends and family.

title: cold cucumber soup with shrimp and crabmeat
directions: Place the cucumbers, Tabasco, onion juice and 1 cup of the buttermilk in a blender or the bowl of a food processor; puree until the mixture is smooth.
Transfer the mixture to a large bowl; whisk in the remaining buttermilk, sour cream and the salt and pepper.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix soup, oil, sugar and vinegar together (reserve 1 cup for later).

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° in tube pan.
Cool 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: beatlenut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut, pecan and oats.
Beat well.
Add pecans, oats and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add brown sugar.
Chip orange slices and nuts in flour; mix and then combine with egg mixture.
Roll out or drop onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade liver mush
directions: Put all items, except corn meal, in a pot and cover with water.
Cook until done.
Cool.
Remove all bones and skin. Grind all meat.
Place back in pot with the juice and heat, adding the corn meal to the mixture while it is cooking until it becomes a consistent mixture.
You may need to add more water.
When mixture is thick and smooth, pour into loaf pans and let cool.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Spoon on wax paper to cool.
You can also make and leave out the nuts if you wish to.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Measure 1/2 cup tomato sauce from the can; add to Grape-Nuts flakes cereal.
Mix in ground beef, chopped onion, eggs, salt and oregano.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Heat remaining tomato sauce; spoon over loaf.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk on medium heat until it reaches a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered oblong pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fruit salad(serves 6)
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice on apple slices.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: baked pork chops with apples
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cut apples into 1-inch slices.
Place chops in casserole.
Top with apples.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and sugar.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.

title: french dressing(diabetic recipe)
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl; beat with a beater for 1/2 minute.
Pour into a container.
Cover; refrigerate until used. Bring back to room temperature; shake well before using.
Allow 2 tablespoons per serving.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Chop green peppers and onion.
Saute in 1 teaspoon of butter until peppers are tender and onions are transparent, then set aside.
Boil chicken breasts in water until done, approximately 15 minutes.
While chicken breasts are cooking, mix together cream of chicken soup with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
When mixed, add onion and peppers.
Remove chicken breasts from water when done.
May leave whole or pull meat apart into strips.

Place chicken in baking dish, pour soup mixture on top and add shredded cheese on top. Crush tortilla chips and sprinkle enough on top of cheese to cover. Bake in 350° oven until mixture bubbles and cheese is melted, approximately 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: southern fried squash
directions: Wash squash and slice into saucepan.
Cover with water, add salt and boil until tender.
Fry bacon, set aside.
Leave enough grease in frying pan to cover bottom of pan.
Chop onion and brown in bacon grease.
Drain squash and add to onion.
Break slices of bacon up into squash.
Stir and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar and stir.
Let simmer on medium heat until excess juice is absorbed, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet; add all other ingredients, except cheeses, and simmer slowly (with lid on).
Grease casserole dishes and begin layering:
noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese, American cheese and Cheddar or Bleu cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with a layer of American or Cheddar cheese.

title: aunt jean's apple nut coffee cake
directions: Melt butter in glass baking dish. Mix in Karo and brown sugar. Layer walnuts then sliced apples in baking dish then sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Place biscuits on top. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes. Invert on a plate and serve warm.

title: bean beef casserole
directions: In skillet, brown meat, grilled done.
Add onions and stir until tender.
Add salt and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with cooked beans over meat.
Prepare corn bread mix; carefully spread batter over beans and bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Chop vegetables in food processor.
Cover with the salt.
Let stand overnight.
On the second day, drain and rinse with clear water and drain again.
While the vegetables are draining, mix together in a large stainless steel pot the sugars, vinegar and spices.
Add vegetables and cook for 1 hour.
Fill sterilized jars with the relish.
Seal.
No need to process.
Store in a cool place, though.

title: eggplant bake
directions: Mix crumbs, marjoram, oregano and garlic salt.
Dip eggplant in margarine, then in crumb mixture.
Place in single layer in greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).

title: grilled potatoes surprise
directions: Sprinkle with garlic salt and spread butter on top.
Wrap in Reynolds.
Fold and put on grill until potatoes are done.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip and milk.
Cream in the cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Garnish with red cherries, pineapple chunks or serve on lettuce leaf.

title: molasses gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in molasses until smooth.
Stir in eggs and beat well.
Dissolve the soda in cup of hot water and stir into molasses mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and spices. Stir gradually into molasses mixture until well blended.
Add raisins.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix bread crumbs, parsley, oil, sundried tomatoes, capers, garlic and grated cheese.
Fill hollows of tomatoes.
Drizzle with a little oil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until stuffing is golden brown.

title: crockpot cheese souffle
directions: Grease crockpot.
Alternate bread and cheese, starting with bread and ending with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, and salt.
Pour over bread and cheese. Top with paprika.
Cook on high for 30 minutes, then on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: rolled stuffed flank steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Saute butter, carrots, mushrooms and onion for 5 minutes.
Pour in bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, eggs and 1/2 of broth.
Spread evenly on steak.
Roll up like a jelly roll and tie with string.

title: good pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into raw crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over rolled oats; let sit for 1 hour, then add yeast softened in 1 cup warm water followed by remaining ingredients.
Add flour gradually, stirring until dough stiffens, then knead until all flour is absorbed.
Let dough rise in greased bowl until double.
Punch down.
Form into loaves.
Let rise again until double, then bake at 375° until golden brown, approximately 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: salad nicoise
directions: *Tuna fish may be substituted for anchovies.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour butter over chicken.
Heat soup and broth until boiling.
Pour over chicken. Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Spread over chicken. Bake in a 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Make well in the center.
Place oil, unbeaten egg yolks, cold water and orange rind in well; beat with a spoon until smooth.

title: mustard-apricot pork chops
directions: Combine preserves and mustard in a small saucepan; heat until preserves melt, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.	Trim excess fat
from
pork
chops
and
place	chops on a lightly greased broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes; brush chops with half of glaze and turn.
Broil 5 minutes and brush with remaining glaze.
Broil an additional 2 minutes and sprinkle with green onions.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: layered spinach
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Mix baking mix, milk, eggs and onion.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes. Spread in dish.
Mix other ingredients; spoon evenly over batter in dish.
Bake until set, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: fudge mallow candy(microwave)
directions: Cook chocolate and peanut butter 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir after each minute.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted and smooth. Pour into greased pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: incredible edibles
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan as evenly as possible.
Melt a 12 ounce package of semi-sweet chocolate morsels and spread over top.
Let it set at room temperature.
Can be frozen or refrigerated.

title: fat-free crust
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grind granola in food processor for 2 minutes.
Add apple juice concentrate, honey and egg white. Process minimally to blend ingredients, approximately 30 seconds.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles, meat, Ragu sauce and cheese.
Repeat and pour water over all; cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave black forest cake
directions: Grease pan
with
shortening
or Pam.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix
remaining
ingredients well and pour into microwave tube pan.
Bake on High for 13 minutes in microwave. Turn cake around after 7 minutes.

title: old fashioned chicken dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add broth and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Form ball.
Roll dough until 1/16-inch thick.
Using a sharp knife, cut the entire rolled dough into 1-inch strips, then cut crosswise into 1 1/2-inch rectangles.
Drop dumplings into boiling broth.
Cover and cook on medium-low heat 15 minutes, or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice for other use, if desired.

title: spicy walnut raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, corn syrup, margarine and spices with hand mixer until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes until set.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended thoroughly (4 minutes is fine).
Pour blended mixture into a greased Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with vegetables (to dip).

title: brown sugar wafers
directions: Mix first four ingredients until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes or until cookie is brown around edges.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: market bulletin sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients well and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: cocoa drop cookies(unbaked)
directions: Boil all ingredients except oatmeal together 5 minutes.
Mix well with oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and cool.

title: chili pasta grande
directions: Generously spray large skillet with cooking spray.
Heat over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook stirring constantly 2 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, kidney beans, jalapeno pepper, chili powder and cumin.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Toss with elbows.
Serve with sour cream and cilantro.
Makes 4 servings.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate pieces, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until chocolate is melted and blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut when firm.

title: crisp dill pickles(dill pickles are easy to make.  my son, dan, loves them!)
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack as many as possible into sterile gallon glass jars.
In each jar, put dill, garlic toes, mustard seed and alum.
In a kettle, boil vinegar, water and salt for 5 minutes or more.
This makes 3 1/2 gallons.
You may need to double recipe, depending on how many jars you plan on doing.
Pour this mixture into jars and fill to top, then seal.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix the soup and barbecue sauce together and set aside.
Beat the eggs, add milk and break up the bread and add to eggs and milk. Mix together as for meat loaf.
Add 1/4 of the barbecue sauce to the hamburger.
Make into very small balls and cook in oven on cookie sheet.
When done, put in crock-pot and pour remaining sauce over them.
The longer they simmer, the better the flavor.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix the last 2 ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix flour, sugar, oil, eggs, juice, vanilla and baking powder by hand.
Batter will be thick.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Pour in 1/3 batter, 1/3 apples and sprinkle with 1/3 cinnamon mixture.
Repeat, ending with cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: texas-size almond crunch cookies
directions: Combine sugar, powdered sugar, butter and vegetable oil in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs and almond extract, beating well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating just until blended after each addition.
Stir in almonds and brickle chips.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: *Do not whip; use right from envelope.

title: cheese rice krispies
directions: Mix
cheese,
butter
and
Tabasco.
Add
flour and mix well. Add Krispies.
Shape into balls (walnut size) and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each with a fork and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Then spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes (no longer) at 400°.
Mix together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Mix together jello with boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries (chop or slice large berries).
Let stand 10 minutes, then add this on top of "whip mix".
Refrigerate until set.

title: rapid mix-sweet dough
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add margarine.
Gradually add water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour or enough to make a thick batter.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead the dough until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap, then with a towel and let rest 20 minutes.
Prepare as desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake tart
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch tart pan.
In blender, process cookies and butter until crumbly.
Press in pan, then refrigerate.
Blend cheese, eggs, vanilla, almond extract and honey in blender.
Spoon filling into tart shell.
Bake until firm, 30 minutes, at 350°. Garnish with fruit before serving.

title: hungarian chili egg puff (brunch)
directions: In mixer bowl, beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and melted butter, blending well.
Stir in chilies.
Pour into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a pan and bring to rolling boil.
Boil one minute and 15 seconds.
Remove from heat. Stir in oatmeal,
vanilla
and
peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: strawberry snow
directions: Whip the egg whites until stiff, while adding the salt and cream of tartar.
Carefully fold in strawberries.
Add sweetener to taste.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put the sugar and milk in a heavy pan (it burns easily) over medium heat and keep stirring.
Let come to a rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Put the marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla in a large bowl.
Pour cooked mixture over marshmallows and peanut butter. Stir in really well.
This sets quickly.
Pour into greased pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Stir until stiff.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
