Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: black-eyed pea cakes
directions: Saute onion, garlic, bell pepper and jalapenos in butter.
In a bowl, combine them with the remaining ingredients and chill about an hour.
Form small patties from the batter and coat them with yellow cornmeal.
Fry in vegetable oil in a skillet until browned. Serve with salsa.
Yield:
10 cakes.

title: blowing bubbles
directions: Gently mix, trying to avoid making bubbles on the surface. The less bubbles on the surface of the mixture, the stronger the bubbles will be.
Different sized circular objects (even 6-pack plastic rings) make for great bubble fun!

title: elephant soup
directions: Mix 1 1/2 ounces rum with Coke; drink.
Wash and dry elephant (don't use shampoo as this will spoil the flavor).
Chop into bite size pieces.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until ice cubes are crushed (about 1/2 minute).

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. Cut pineapple in half and scoop pulp.
Fill in cheese mixture. Serve with crackers and raspberry preserves.

title: hot mushroom spread
directions: Saute chopped onions in butter.
Add to the cream cheese. Blend well, then add chopped mushrooms, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Spoon into an ovenproof dish. Bake at 375°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients and add zucchini.
Pour into loaf tins and bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: fruit medley salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together gently and chill.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger (with onions, if you wish).
Add taco mix and refried beans; simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Put half of this in a 2 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put meat mixture and torn up tortilla shells in layers, then put remaining soup mixture on top.
Add some cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Add more cheese and melt.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, onions and some salsa.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, margarine, onion, green pepper, water, salt and pepper in skillet.
Cover; cook for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in cheese and milk; simmer and stir occasionally until cheese melts.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix everything, including melted oleo, in bowl.
Pour into pan and bake at 450° until brown on top.

title: irish feast
directions: Put brisket in a 12-quart stockpot and fill with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 to 4 1/2 hours until tender.
Cut cabbage into quarters and add to brisket.
Add potatoes and cook for about 30 minutes.
Add corn and cook 15 minutes.
This is super easy and good for keeping
you out of the kitchen all day!
It's an Irish tradition to cook this on St. Patrick's Day.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: For bar cookie crust:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9 inch baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl with mixer, at medium speed, beat flour, margarine, sugar and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbles.
Press firmly into bottom of pan and 1/4 inch up sides of pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with
desired filling.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: You will need a 10-inch pie crust pan.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Combine and toss with seeds. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.

title: crackling bread
directions: *Cracklings are the pieces of meat remaining after the lard has been rendered from the pork fat.

title: hot beer rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, beans and Spanish rice. Simmer about 10 to 20 minutes.
Put a layer of meat mixture, Fritos and cheese and sprinkle with garlic salt,
Repeat.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with green salad and buttered, garlic sprinkled French bread.

title: salted nut roll bar
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Put in oven until marshmallows are puffy, not brown.

title: chicken chinoise(serves 6)
directions: Cut the chicken into bite-sized pieces. Heat the oil to very hot in a wok or large skillet.
Add the chicken and cook for 1 minute.
Add the rest of the vegetables and ginger.
Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Add the chicken stock.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate milk. Add milk.
Pour into 4-quart ice cream freezer and freeze according to instructions.
Let harden 1 hour before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: shoo-fly pie(makes 2 pies.)
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter like pie crust.
Reserve 2 cups of the crumbs for topping.
Add to remaining of crumbs the eggs, molasses or syrup and 1 1/2 cups hot tap water.
Mix well. Dissolve in 1/2 cup hot water the soda.
Add to other ingredients. Put into 2 unbaked pie shells. Add crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes until set.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt. Add milk to slightly beaten egg yolks. Combine flour mixture and milk mixture. Cook in top of double boiler until consistency of custard. Add vanilla. Line baking dish with vanilla wafers. Slice bananas over wafers. Pour 1/2 the custard over bananas. Cover with remaining custard. Beat egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar. Beat until stiff. Pour on top of pudding. Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until delicately browned. Serve hot or cold. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tater dipped chicken
directions: Dip chicken in mixture of egg and water. Season to taste. Roll in potato flakes.
Place chicken in melted butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Turn once after 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free holiday nog
directions: Combine pudding mix, 2 cups of cold milk, vanilla and sugar substitute in a bowl. Mix according to pudding directions. Pour into a 1/2-gallon container with a tight-fitting lid. Add 3 cups milk and shake well. Add evaporated milk and shake. Add remaining milk; shake well. Chill. Yield: 8 servings.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in the microwave for 3 minutes.
Take it out and mix peanuts and marshmallows.
Mix very well.
Put this mixture on a 9 x 13-inch dish that is greased with oil and put in the freezer for 20 minutes, covered.
After that, take it out of the freezer and cut in pieces and it is ready to serve. "Good appetite!"

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, mix eggs and sugar about 2 minutes.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Brown chicken
in butter;
place in casserole dish.
If using fresh mushrooms, saute in remaining butter and pour over chicken. Blend sour cream, soup and Marsala; heat in skillet. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle	with
paprika.	Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.	Garnish
with
parsley and serve over rice or noodles.

title: new england brown bread
directions: *To sour milk, place 2 tablespoons of vinegar in a measuring cup; add enough milk to make 2 cups and let stand for a couple of minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Take chicken off bones and cut into small pieces.
Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix celery soup and broth together and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, egg and margarine with milk.
Add vegetables and pour over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: baked sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Arrange sprouts in shallow baking dish.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper; blend well.
Pour over sprouts and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until sprouts are tender.
(If possible, marinate sprouts in vinegar 1/2 hour to 1 hour before baking.)

title: caramel-chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces; drizzle with caramel.
Set aside.
In a bowl, beat the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add eggs, beating on low just until combined.
Pour over caramel in crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until center appears set.
Cool.
Chill, covered, for at least an hour before serving. Sift cocoa lightly over pie.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiffened.
Then beat yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir first mixture gradually into yolks. Fold in whites, asparagus, onion and pimiento.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish, place in pan of hot water and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve at once.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove mushroom stems, keeping caps. Chop enough stems to measure 1 cup; put in bowl.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
In saucepan, bring water to boil and lemon juice. Add caps; cook 1 minute.
Drain.
Spoon cheese mixture into caps. Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: el gondo
directions: Brown meat and spices to taste (salt, pepper and garlic salt). Add can of tomatoes and chili mix. Cook yellow rice according to directions.
Layer meat, then rice in casserole dish.
Heat soup and milk.
Pour over meat and rice.
Put onions, olives, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese on top. Top with Fritos.

title: good morning pumpkin pancakes(makes about 16 pancakes)
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Add milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup batter (depending on size of pancake desired) onto heated and slightly greased griddle.
Cook until top surface is bubbly and edges are dry.
Turn; cook until golden. Keep pancakes warm.
Serve with syrup or honey.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dice onion and crush garlic.
In frypan, brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Once meat is browned, drain if meat is fatty.
Add steak sauce and Worcestershire sauce; stir in evenly.

title: seven minute white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, egg whites (at room temperature), syrup and cream of tartar in top of a large double boiler; add water and beat on low speed of electric mixer for 3 seconds or just until blended.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mold ingredients together excluding walnuts. Roll in crushed walnuts after molded into a ball or log shaped form.

title: easy taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.

title: barron's brownies
directions: Adjust a rack 1/3 up from bottom of oven.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Place both chocolates and butter in a 3-quart heavy pan over medium heat.
Stir until melted.
Whisk if needed until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt, vanilla, sugar and eggs, one at a time, stirring after each egg is added until fully blended.
Add flour and stir briskly 1 minute, until mixture is smooth and shiny and comes away from sides of pan, then stir in nuts.
Turn an 8-inch square pan over.
Center a 12-inch square of aluminum foil, shiny side down over pan.
Fold down sides and corners to shape of pan.
Remove and place foil inside pan and paint melted butter on the foil.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely in pan, then place pan in freezer for about an hour until cake is firm.
Cover with a cutting board and turn pan. Remove foil. Quarter cake and cut quarters into quarters.
When they are served cold, they have a caramel texture.

title: drumstick dessert
directions: Mix 2/3 cup peanuts, wafers and oleo together; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Layer over crust.
Mix pudding and milk; pour over cream cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with remaining nuts and candy bar.
Refrigerate.

title: gert gurganus sweet milk cornbread
directions: Sift together the corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg.
Add milk; add to first mixture.
Add shortening.
Pour into hot, greased 10-inch skillet or pan, muffin pan or corn stick pan.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: creamy vegetable rice bake
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Mix well. Add the rest of your dry ingredients.
Add nuts and currants. Pour into 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until done.
Freeze or serve hot.

title: apple rolls
directions: Roll dough out the size of a plate.
Put apples, sugar and pats of butter on dough.
Sprinkle with vanilla.
Roll into a roll and place in well-greased pan.
May repeat for as many rolls as you want.
Bake in oven for 40 minutes or until well done at 350°. Remove from oven.
Mix 2 cups milk, 1 1/2 cups sugar and vanilla. Pour over apple rolls.
Return to oven about 30 minutes or until thickened.
Serve while hot.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and gradually beat in well beaten eggs. Cook over low heat and stir constantly until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add salad dressing. Combine rest of ingredients and pour on dressing.
Toss.

title: favorite icing(best cake decorating frosting.)
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients together.
Beat on high speed for 5 minutes.

title: snow cap
directions: In an 8 ounce coffee glass, add Bailey's, Goldschlager and fill with cocoa, whipped cream and cinnamon stick as garnish.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer each ingredient; do not mix.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, butter and 1 cup sugar.
Bake in pizza pan or other flat pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Put on top of cooled crust.
Put strawberry slices on top of cream cheese mixture.
Put glaze on top of strawberries.

title: sue's kale soup
directions: Start soup bones in 4 qt. water, add bay leaves.
Simmer until meat on
bones is done. Remove, cut off
meat and return to pot. Discard bone (or give to Fido).
Add linguica and chourico along with beef broth and can of tomatoes.
Simmer for one hour, then remove bay leaves.
Add carrots, onion, frozen kale, shredded cabbage and simmer for one hour.
Add potatoes and continue cooking until the potatoes are tender. Fresh Kale alone with the liquid its cooked in may be substituted for frozen.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned pie pastry (canada)
directions: Blend flour and lard until mealy. In measuring cup, blend egg, salt, sugar and vinegar. Add enough water to make 1 cup. Combine with flour mixture. This will make dough for 6 to 9-inch pies. It freezes well in balls of dough.

title: hot mulled rosy tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags, sugar, orange slices and spices.
Stir to dissolve sugar; cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat cranberry-apple drink.
Combine with tea.
Remove tea bags and serve hot.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts or six 7 ounce servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients as for cake, except apples.
Put apples in last.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Add all ingredients to the sugar and cream cheese mixture. Mix well and freeze.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except nuts and chocolate chips.
Fold them in last.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift together 2 tablespoons flour, 1/8 teaspoon salt and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg and beat to a smooth thin batter.
Blend in diced apples and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes. Make a topping with the remaining sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Sprinkle over pie and brown in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: monterey jack cheese spread
directions: Combine Monterey Jack cheeses, Miracle Whip, margarine, green onions, garlic powder and black pepper; mix thoroughly.
Split bread loaf lengthwise; spread cut surface of both halves with cheese mixture.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 400° until bubbly and slightly brown.
Cut into serving pieces.
Serve hot.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Rinse chicken and cook in salted water until done.
Cut or tear in small pieces.
Cut grapes in half.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add chicken, celery and grapes; mix well.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and it's ready to serve.
Makes a great vegetable dip.

title: roast goose
directions: Dress the fowl 24 hours before using and soak in salt water 2 hours before cooking.
Make a mashed potato dressing, seasoned with onion, butter, pepper and salt.
Fill the body of the goose; grease it all over well with butter and dredge with flour.
Place in pan with a pint of water.
Baste well and cook 2 hours.
Serve with onion gravy and applesauce.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar; let cool. Combine all ingredients and freeze. When ready to serve, let thaw to mushy stage and add ginger ale. Serves 30.

title: candied ham balls
directions: Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Chill.
Brown in a lightly greased skillet, then place in a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish. Cover with sauce and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding(makes 4 servings)
directions: For Cream Pie Filling, add 1 teaspoon butter or 1 teaspoon margarine.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars together.
Mix in rest of ingredients well.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar or decorative sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: strawberry salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: The size and individual amounts of the salad is up to you.

title: seven-up gelatin
directions: Mix and cool the top 3 ingredients.
Fold in pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into loaf pan (11 x 7-inch).
Refrigerate until set.

title: sloppy joe sandwiches
directions: Heat frying pan on high.
Brown hamburger and add salt and pepper, then add catsup.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: angie's broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli according
to
directions;
drain.
Place spears in oblong baking dish.
Crumble crackers over broccoli. In saucepan mix soup, cream cheese, margarine and lemon juice. Heat on low until
cheese
melts.
Pour
sauce
over broccoli. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese
over
broccoli
and sauce.
Place in 350° oven until hot.

title: crab quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche pan with pastry.
Place a piece of buttered foil, buttered side down, over pastry.
Gently press into pastry shell.
Cover foil with a layer of dried peas or beans. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove foil and peas.
Prick shell and bake 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat and boil until thick and drops like jelly.
Bake crust. Pile strawberries in crust.
Pour cold sauce over.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with sugar mixture.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 300° for about 11 minutes.

title: mama's dumplings
directions: Make as for biscuits, mixing sifted flour, grease and milk, adding enough water to make dough fairly stiff.
Roll out on floured board or pastry sheet to about 3/8-inch thick.
Cut in long strips 1-inch wide.
Heat broth.
If not enough broth, add water to make real thin when adding strips (crisscrossed) into broth.
Add more salt and pepper if desired.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally until dumplings are well done.
Add meat to dumplings if desired.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: toffee bars
directions: Grease baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until very light brown.
(Crust will be soft.)
Remove from oven. Immediately distribute chocolate chips on crust.
When chocolate is soft, spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
While warm, cut into bars about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: different pumpkin bread
directions: In large mix, mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and spice.
Add eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Add nuts, raisins and chips.
Divide into 3 well-greased loaf pans or 6 mini-pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Drizzle top with melted chocolate chips while warm.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In bowl, combine French dressing, mayonnaise, salt and mustard; mix well.
Stir in celery, pickle, eggs and shrimp. Cover and refrigerate.

title: liz's baked fish creole
directions: Saute onion in butter until limp but not browned.
Add rest of the ingredients except fish.
Simmer for 5 minutes to combine flavors.
Place fish fillets in a baking dish and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing for 2 to 4 hours.
Grill breasts until done.
Discard leftover dressing.

title: libby's fast no bake cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip to mixture.
Put in pie crust and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Pie filling may be added to top just before serving.

title: microwave pecan pralines
directions: Combine both sugars and water and stir until dissolved.
Place in microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Stir; cook 3 more minutes. Stir; cook 2 more minutes.
Remove and stir in margarine and nuts. Cook until starts to thicken.
Quickly drop on waxed paper for desired size.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Stir 1 tablespoon flour in chopped nuts before mixing.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Preheat oven to 300°. Get at room temperature the Crisco and margarine.

title: spicy pepper steak
directions: Brown onions, peppers and mushrooms in oil.
Then brown steak on both sides.
Put in crock-pot and add tomatoes and enough water to cover meat and vegetables.
Cook all day or all night until meat is tender.
Then add rice and gravy mix.
Stir this until mixed well.
Cook about 30 minutes more until rice is tender. Serves 4 to 5.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour dough into four 1 pound coffee cans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or perhaps a little longer until done.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In heavy 2-quart pan, cook rice in water and salt 15 minutes. After it starts to boil, remove from heat and add milk and raisins.
Gradually add beaten eggs, one at a time, stirring briskly while over low heat. Stir constantly until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nutmeg.

title: dunkin' platters
directions: 1. Melt butter over low heat.

Mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl. 2. Add beaten eggs, vanilla, melted butter and mix together with a wooden spoon or hands. 3. Drop big spoonful on ungreased pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Process for 1/2 minute or until cubes are crushed. Makes five 8 ounce servings.
Top if desired with scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O's together according to package directions.
Let gel until slightly thickened.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Beat on slow speed with mixer until well mixed.
Blend in pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: quick breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over layers.
Put in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: tortilla stack
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix turkey, 1/2 cup salsa, beans, dressing, onions, tomatoes and seasonings in saucepan.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat 10 minutes or until thickened. Place 2 tortillas on cookie sheet.
Spread 3/4 cup of turkey mixture to edge of each tortilla.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with tortilla.
Top each stack with remaining salsa.
Bake 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Cut each stack into quarters.
Top with lettuce, sour cream, tomato, cilantro and additional cheese, if desired.
Makes 8 servings (2 stacks).

title: fruchtekuchen (fruit kuchen)
directions: *Use fresh, frozen or canned; be creative.
Example: Apricots, peaches, pears, Italian prunes, apples, rhubarb (increase sugar).

title: beans and beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Brown meat in a medium size skillet. Drain off fat.
Add onion, garlic, bell peppers and tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Add beans and chili powder.
Spoon mixture into sprayed baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover. Bake 20 minutes more.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: steak and potatoes in oven
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces; coat well with flour.
Brown in oleo.
Add salt, pepper and onions.
Cover with sliced potatoes; add hot water to cover.
Put in hot oven (400°) and bake for 1 hour, or until potatoes are done and gravy thickens.

title: lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger with onion. Drain and add spaghetti sauce. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and corn meal.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon juice and rind and the melted butter. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cream together cheese, butter, mayonnaise and garlic salt; fold in crab meat.
Spread on each half of muffin.
Chill 5 minutes in freezer.
Cut muffins into quarters; bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Can be frozen up to 3 weeks in advance.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk with wire whisk or lowest setting on mixer, about 30 seconds.
Add lemonade and beat with whisk for 30 more seconds.
Mixture will be thick.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Store in refrigerator overnight or at least 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with lemon slice curls if desired.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender; remove from broth. Add parsley, celery seed, onion and bouillon cubes.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into small pieces; bring to a boil.
Add chicken and noodles and cook until noodles are tender.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Cook potato in microwave.
Prick potato with fork before cooking.
Cook until done.
Mix with 1 tablespoon butter (you don't have to use butter if you don't want to).
Peel potato before mixing with butter.
Add salt, pepper and egg; mix well.

title: fried green beans
directions: Place 1/2 pound of bacon in skillet on medium-high heat until grease covers bottom of skillet.
Remove bacon and cover.
Place 1 pound of green beans in skillet at same heat for about 35 minutes or until beans start to turn brown.
Cut strips of bacon in half. Place back in skillet; season with salt and pepper.
When bacon is done, the beans are done.
Repeat process for the remaining of the ingredients.
Makes enough for 2 to 4 people.

title: chocolate mix
directions: Sift together all ingredients.
Store in 3-pound coffee can or canister.
Mix 4 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix to 1 cup of hot water or to taste.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients. Cut shortening with pastry blender until resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk and mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 to 4 times.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar well, add oil, nuts and eggs.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Bake in a 9x13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients; put in buttered dish.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Add water if necessary to make 2 cups.
Heat juice to boiling.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add Coca-Cola and fruit.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with salad dressing, cream cheese dressing or whipped cream.

title: oyster stew
directions: Carefully pick over oysters to remove bits of shell.
In deep skillet or kettle, heat butter until sizzling.
Add oysters with liquid, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, pepper, salt and paprika.
Heat until edges of oysters; curl slightly.
Add milk. Heat quickly but do not boil.
Serve in bowls topped with paprika and lumps of butter and oyster crackers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Remove seeds from the peppers and some of the seeds and pulp from the tomatoes.
Grind the tomatoes, onions and green peppers together.
Drain and discard the juice.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard and celery seed together.
Stir into tomato mixture in a saucepan; boil until done, about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, sterilize 8 pint jars.
Pack jars with relish and seal.

title: ensaladillo rusa(spanish potato salad)
directions: Prepare the potatoes.
Peel, wash and boil.
Chill and cut into very small cubes. Chop the asparagus (saving several for use as decoration). Mix the chopped asparagus, peas, olives, chopped red pimentos, tuna and chopped eggs.
Add mayonnaise and enough asparagus juice until texture desired is reached.
Add the potatoes and salt. Add more mayonnaise and asparagus juice, if needed.
Arrange on serving platter and decorate with asparagus spears, pimento strips, olives and egg wedges. Chill.
Has a creamy texture.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine all ingredients - I put this in my electric skillet on low and keep stirring every 10 minutes for about 30 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, beaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir and add this to creamed mixture.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll very thin and cut out cookies with cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400°.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: angel dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add 2 cups milk.
Blend in pudding.
Stir in fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Pour in dish and chill at least 2 hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough water to mixture until thin enough to pour.
Grease pan well.
Sprinkle little cornmeal in pan.
Bake at 500° until brown.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In a saucepan, put peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add pectin and food coloring.
Stir well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: sweet chex mix
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a very large bowl.
Boil sugar, syrup and margarine together for 2 minutes; add vanilla. Pour over Chex mix and mix well.
Spread on kitchen counter.
Add sunflower seeds and mix in.
Allow to dry on counter turning frequently.
Can also dry on cookie sheets in 200° oven turning frequently for crispier mix.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make at least 12 hours before serving.
Mix all ingredients well.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts or pecans, cut fine, just before serving.

title: make ahead holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes; add cream cheese in small pieces and then the butter; beat well.
Add sour cream.
To the milk, add the eggs and onion; add to the potatoes mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Place in greased 9-inch casserole and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned on top.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Next mix half of Cool Whip and cream cheese with sugar and spread over first layer.
Next, mix the pudding mixes according to directions.
Layer chocolate pudding, then layer vanilla pudding.
Finish by spreading remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, a little at a time; beat until fluffy and light. Add flour, Crisco oil and spices. Stir in apples, nuts and chips. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: best meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients, except sauces and rice.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Bake in glass square pan about 10 to 15 minutes until browned.

title: meatloaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes

title: delicious healthy chili
directions: Soak pinto beans overnight or add 2 inches water above beans. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Let stand for 1 hour. Drain.
Add more water until 2 inches above beans and add 1 tablespoon salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 to 4 hours. Add water as needed.

title: italian fried bread and eggs
directions: Combine slightly beaten eggs, cheese, margarine and seasonings.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Dip bread, 1 slice at a time, into milk, but do not soak, then dip in seasoned eggs. Saute in hot oil until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 3.
Excellent as a Lenten side dish.

title: quick one-dish supper
directions: Bring soup and water to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in Minute rice.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in butter.
Set aside.
Put a layer of Tater Tots in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour meat mixture, green beans and water chestnuts over Tater Tots.
Pour soups over next.
Cover top with another layer of Tater Tots and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fried bananas
directions: Peel and cut banana into 1/4-inch slices.
Melt the shortening over medium heat.
Fry banana until brown and crispy.
Turn and fry the other side.

title: oreo crumble dessert
directions: Mix cookies and butter together; press into bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream together until soft. Pour over cookie mixture.
Chill until pudding mixture is firm. Soften Cool Whip and spread over top of pudding mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Oreo cookies over Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Put into crock-pot. Stir together. Cook on low 8 to 12 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with potatoes or rice or over noodles.

title: blueberry stack cake
directions: Mix Duncan Hines Butter Recipe cake mix, eggs, milk and peanut oil together.
Pour into 3 or 4 layers; cook as directed.
Cool.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Place all ingredients together in a saucepan and heat on medium heat. Stir until it thickens, the remove.
Dribble over desserts.

title: cheesy rice
directions: Mix together in oven dish with lid, top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: fried apples
directions: Place apples, sugar and water in skillet. When apples begin to cook, turn on medium heat and cook until apples begin to brown. Remove from heat before they begin to stick. Serve hot with fresh butter and hot biscuits.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Some ovens may vary

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and coconut.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
While hot, spread with a large jar of marshmallow cream and let cool.

title: broccoli cheesy chicken
directions: In frying pan over medium heat in hot butter, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: pears thornhill
directions: Peel, core and halve pears.
In a pot, bring water and sugar to simmer.
Add pears, simmer 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Cool pears in syrup.
Drain pears, then fill center of 6 halves with chocolate yogurt and the others with vanilla yogurt.
Top with whipped cream and chocolate.

title: mock apple pie(delicious with ice cream)
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with crust.
In saucepan over high heat, heat water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind; cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place remaining crust over pie.
Trim, seal and flute edges.
Slit top crust for steam to escape.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is crisp and golden.

title: bacony creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach by boiling or in microwave.
Drain well and squeeze out as much moisture as possible.
Chop fine, using food processor or food grinder.
Cook bacon in skillet until crisp. Remove and drain.
Crumble and reserve.
In about 2 tablespoons of the bacon fat, saute garlic and onion over medium heat.
When onion is limp, add spinach.
Lower heat.
Season with salt and pepper; stir well as moisture evaporates from spinach, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Sprinkle in flour, stirring constantly until smooth. Gradually stir in cream or milk and cook until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in spinach mixture and heat through.
Remove from heat, stir in reserved bits of bacon, and serve.
Serves 4.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown your hamburg; drain well.
In a crock-pot, put hamburg, ketchup, onion and celery, chopped.
The longer it simmers the better this gets.
Will make 12 to 14 hamburg buns full.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute sausage and chicken in oil until lightly browned.
Remove and keep warm.
In the drippings, saute celery, onion, green pepper, green onions and garlic until tender. Add tomatoes, thyme, salt, pepper and cayenne and cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in broth, rice, water and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in sausage and chicken; heat through.

title: fudge cake
directions: Use a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan (oiled).
Sift together on waxed paper the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Beat until light and fluffy (3 minutes) the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Along with flour mixture, add the water.
Beat all until smooth; spread evenly in pan.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with chocolate icing.
Cut into 24 pieces.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans according to package directions. Drain. Mix remaining ingredients and combine with beans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed pears milanese
directions: Blend powdered sugar, cherries and almonds together.
Fill pears with this mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Pour sherry over pears and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until pears are done, but not too soft.
Serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: date dainties
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spread into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been greased with margarine.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake, or they will become hard and tough.
Cool slightly; cut into squares or strips.

title: party dream salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat together the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt until light and fluffy.
Fold in bananas, pineapple, oranges, cherries, pecans and whipped cream.
Turn into a 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm (12 to 24 hours).
Unmold.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serves 10 to 12.
(This salad may also be chilled in an oblong baking dish.)

title: pudding salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, liquid and pudding mix. Fold in rest of ingredients. Serve chilled.

title: pasta rolls
directions: Remove casing from sausage; crumble sausage into frying pan; cook until brown.
In another frying pan, brown ground beef.
Add browned beef to browned sausage.
Drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce and 1/2 cup Romano cheese.

title: sausage-potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°, or use microwave on High.
Place peeled and cubed potatoes in covered container with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 cup of water.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Drain; add remaining ingredients, except sausage.
Mix lightly; spoon into an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with the smoked sausage, cut into equal portions.
Bake for 30 minutes in oven or for 8 to 10 minutes in the microwave.
Place 3 diagonally cut American cheese slices on sausages.
Bake or microwave until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: primavera pasta salad
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a large bowl, tossing gently. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a jar. Cover lightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over pasta mixture.
Toss well to coat.
Let stand at room temperature one hour to blend flavors. Cover and chill one hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: red cabbage
directions: Remove the coarse outer leaves.
Cut into 4 sections.
Remove the hard core.
Wash and shred finely.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients.
Place dough in covered bowl in refrigerator.
No need to let rise before baking.
Bake as for biscuits.

title: 20 minute chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables, onion and celery in water until tender, then drain.
Mix together mayonnaise and 1/2 cup cheese. Combine with vegetables and pour into greased casserole.
Mix together cracker crumbs, margarine and 1/2 cup cheese. Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or pork chop casserole
directions: Put pork chops or chicken in shallow dish.
Mix rice, water, salt, pepper, onion, undiluted soup and pepper; pour over meat. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until done.

title: anna's happy face pancakes
directions: First you get the pancake.

Then you put 2 dots for eyes with whipped cream and then put a dot for the nose with whipped cream. Put a mouth with the whipped cream, then take candy corn (or any small food) and put 2 in the whipped cream of the eyes.
Then put a candy corn on the nose and then put as many candy corns as you can on the mouth and eat!

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving sized pieces.
Dip in flour, salt and pepper and brown in oil.
Combine vegetables, water and sugar and pour over steak.
Cover; reduce heat to 200° and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken sauce for gravy (1 1/2 c. water mixed with 4 tbsp. flour).

title: sherbet macaroons
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and chopped nuts with whipped topping.
Put one-half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of lime sherbet, then a layer of pineapple or orange sherbet.
Finish with the other one-half of the whipped topping mixture.
Freeze several hours or overnight before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Cool and add vanilla, salt, oats and peanut butter.
Stir well and drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook pudding as directed; let cool.
Mix sugar and peanut butter until fine crumbs.
Sprinkle most in pie crust.
Pour vanilla pie filling over crumbs.
When completely cool, cover with Cool Whip.
Spread remaining crumbs on top.

title: moist carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done (30 to 40 minutes).
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pesto mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan and saute garlic until soft but not browned.
Slice off mushroom stems at base of cap.
Brush mushrooms with garlic butter mixture and place in an ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix cream cheese and pesto together and mound in center of each cap.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, bake in a 400 degree oven for five to six minutes or until filling is soft and mushrooms are warm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add bananas and buttermilk. Dissolve soda in butter; mix well.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour and salt.
Mix well; fold in pecans.
Bake at 350° in 1 large or 2 small greased and floured pans, about 45 minutes.
Bread is done when lightly browned or a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes; run knife around loaf to loosen it from pan; lift out.
Cool on wire rack.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour eggs over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add flour a little at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Remove wing tips and discard.
Split wings in half at joint. Broil or bake wing sections until almost cooked.
In deep saucepan, melt margarine.
Add Durkee red hot sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Stir in cayenne pepper.
Mix well over medium heat.
Add partially cooked wing sections and simmer, covered, turning once, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove wings from sauce and serve.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Remove 2/3 cup cake mix to be used later.
In remaining cake mix, add 1 egg and melted butter.
Mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with shortening.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix corn syrup, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, remaining cake mix and pecans.
Pour over crust and place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly (maybe overnight).
Cut into bite size squares.

title: rice consomme
directions: Saute onion and butter together until tender.
Bring water to a boil; add cubes and dissolve.
Add rice, onion and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well; pour into a casserole.
Cover and bake at 350°; stir occasionally.
Bake uncovered the last 10 minutes.

title: beef flambe
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Remove bacon and fry sirloin tip until browned.
Add remaining ingredients, except brandy.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes, until sauce thickens and vegetables are tender.
Heat up 1/4 cup brandy.
Pour meat mixture over rice.
At table, set brandy aflame and pour over meat.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with boiling water or coffee.
Place in refrigerator for an hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet and place a nut or raisin in the center of each cookie.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: butterscotch lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1/2 cup chopped nuts; press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cookies and add 1 stick melted margarine.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Add the mixture to cream cheese mixture. Layer cookies and mixture.
Layer cookies on bottom, then pudding, etc.
End up with cookies on top.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Place butter and vanilla in medium bowl.
Cream with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating 1 minute.
Stop and scrape bowl.
Add eggs and beat 30 seconds.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour over melted butter. Layer fruit on top. Bake at 400° until it browns.

title: bavarian apple cheesecake(dietetic!)
directions: Crumble pie crust stick until it resembles meal; combine with nuts.
Sprinkle with hot water and stir with a fork until mixture holds together and forms a ball.
Press with fingers into greased pie plate or greased bottom of spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine carrots, celery and green onions with water and boil for about 5 minutes.
Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Add flour and whip until smooth.
Blend onion and flour mixture with milk and add to first ingredients.
Add the broth, cheese whiz and seasonings.
Cook over low heat.

title: green beans mediterranean style
directions: Wash the beans, then trim and cut in 2-inch lengths.
In a wide frying pan, cook onion in oil over high heat, stirring until onion is soft but not brown.

Add green pepper and celery; cook over moderate heat, covered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the beans to the cooking vegetables with the water; continue to cook, covered, over moderate heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hot pineapple pie
directions: Grease baking dish.
Drain pineapple.
Pour in dish.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is good hot after cooked.
(Refrigerate leftovers; good even cold.)

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in a large pot.
Mix all other ingredients well in a very large bowl.
Pour melted mixture over popcorn mixture and blend well.
(Butter or grease spoon so it won't stick to mixture.)
Pour mixture into well-greased tube pan and press.
Turn pan upside-down when ready to serve.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: In crock-pot put vegetables in first, then soup, water, salt and pepper.
Put chicken on the top.
Cook on high 1 1/2 hours, then turn to slow for a few more hours until tender.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Divide popped corn and peanuts between 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans. Cook corn syrup, margarine and sugar over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over corn and nut mixture; stir well to mix.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove; let cool on wax paper.
Break apart.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Cook noodles.
Place noodles, chicken and cooked broccoli in baking dish.
Add chicken gravy, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: hamburger and vegetable meal
directions: Tear heavy-duty aluminum foil into four pieces.
Place one hamburger patty on each piece of foil.
Divide vegetables into four piles and add to patty.
Close foil tightly and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: "best in the west" bean bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Combine all except beans.
Mix well.
Then add beans to mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: puffy german pancake
directions: Heat oven and margarine in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet to 400°.
Combine ingredients and beat 2 minutes until smooth.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until batter has climbed up the sides of the skillet and edges are brown and puffy. Cut into wedges and serve with butter, powdered sugar, lemon juice or syrup.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Cover with washed sauerkraut.
Pour over Thousand Island dressing.
Bake until chicken is done, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove cover. Put Cheddar cheese on top and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, dried beef, onions, Worcestershire, mayonnaise and milk.
Roll into ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick fried rice
directions: In a wok or large heavy skillet, heat the oil. Quickly stir-fry the onion and garlic. Add the chicken and cook a few minutes, until just done. Push chicken to sides. Scramble the eggs in the wok. Push to sides. Add shrimp, mushrooms, bean sprouts, broccoli, parsley and rice. Mix the chicken and eggs and stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes. Add the soy sauce, basil and pepper. Stir-fry for another 2 to 3 minutes. Garnish with green onions and serve.

title: chicken dish
directions: Place cooked chicken in a glass baking dish that will hold it. Crush up 2 or 3 handfuls of potato chips and mix them in with the chicken.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and grains soup
directions: In large pot brown chicken thighs and legs 1/2 at a time 15 minutes.
Set aside.
Drain fat.
To saucepan, add chicken broth, barley, wheat berries, onion, bay leaves and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Return chicken to pot and simmer, covered, over medium heat 30 minutes.
Stir in carrots, green beans and celery. Cook, covered, 15 minutes more or until chicken and grains are tender.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Stir in cream cheese. Cook and stir until cheese melts.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Arrange ground beef in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover ground beef with onion.
Add cream of chicken and spread over onion and ground beef.
Cover top with Tater Tots and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: snackers(herb crackers)
directions: Mix oil, dressing mix, lemon pepper, dill weed and garlic salt.
Pour over oyster crackers.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan in 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir several times during baking. Store in airtight container.
(Can substitute Pepperidge Farm fish or oyster crackers.)

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: In large skillet, fry hamburger and onion until done.
Drain grease.
Add mustard and stir, then add tomato soup, water and brown sugar.
Mix well and simmer for 5 minutes.
The mixture should be a little runny with liquid.
While making the Sloppy Joes, cook macaroni as directed on box.
When macaroni is done, drain.
Pour a layer of macaroni in bottom of a greased casserole. Then pour a layer of Sloppy Joes over top of macaroni.
Sprinkle cheese over Sloppy Joes.
Continue to layer in order.
Make at least 3 layers and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pouding chomeur
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a deep dish.

title: meatballs
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in Worcestershire sauce and broth.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well with hands.
Let mixture stand 10 minutes before shaping into 24 meatballs.
Good with steamed rice or noodles.
Contains 180 calories per serving before pasta.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple.
Mix until thick.
Add sour cream to mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir.
Pour into pie shell.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar until crumbly. Place in baked pie shell.
Reserve 1 tablespoonful for topping. Make vanilla pudding mix and place on top of peanut butter mixture.
After pudding cools, cover with whipped topping. Sprinkle crumbs on top.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix oil, mayonnaise and sugar.
Slice onion and green pepper, separate broccoli and cauliflower.
Pour oil and mayonnaise mixture over vegetables.
Chill.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into ovenproof skillet.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with beef, rice, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in shortening.
Pour off fat. Blend remaining soup, water and mustard.
Pour over meatballs. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place all these ingredients into the 4-quart pan.
Mix well. Cook for about 1 1/2 hours; stir occasionally.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Chop kraut into short pieces.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally at least 24 hours.

title: pizza cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown and drain meat.
Stir in paste, onion and seasonings.
Mixture will be very thick.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin and press over bottom and up sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: presbyterian cake
directions: Pour peaches and juice in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chop peaches slightly and spread evenly.
Sprinkle cake mix and pecans over top of peaches.
Put thin slices of butter over top, covering whole surface.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Stir until well blended.
Pour over Rice Chex and toss to coat.
(Use a large bowl.)
Pour powdered sugar into a clean grocery bag.
Add Rice Chex and shake until well coated.
Let cool.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients well by hand.
Do not use electric mixer.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate about two hours before serving.

title: texas relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken, butter and bread crumbs.
Place in covered bowl and place chicken into mixture. Stir to coat.
Marinate, covered, overnight in refrigerator.

title: don's ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, vanilla and Eagle Brand milk and mix well. Fold into whites of the eggs.
Pour into a 2-quart ice cream freezer.
Finish filling with milk to full line on freezer.

title: choco-mint freeze
directions: Mix finely crushed vanilla wafers with melted margarine. Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: 7 layered mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans with 3 tablespoons green chilies.
Mash avocado with lemon, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning.
Layer in a casserole dish starting with beans, avocado, sour cream mixture, green chilies, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Garnish with olives and serve with tortilla chips.

title: friendship casserole
directions: Blend well.
Serve to everyone you meet.

title: orange cheesecake(microwave)
directions: For crust, in a 7-inch pie plate, cook butter or margarine, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Add crushed graham crackers and 1 tablespoon sugar. Stir until all is moistened.
Press mixture firmly against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 to 1 1/2 minutes or until set, giving pie plate a half-turn after 30 seconds.
Set aside.

title: quick and easy snack
directions: Mix all together.
Spread out on cookie sheet and place in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: dum dum salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix with mixer at medium speed until mixed well.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and flavoring; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand until cool. Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Beat.
Add oatmeal and beat well.
Bake in greased and floured 7 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Crumble and drain.
Place on the bottom of large casserole dish.
Crumble bread over sausage.
Blend eggs, mustard, salt and pepper with half and half.
Pour mixture over sausage and bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, cover with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves approximately 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in very small amount of water with salt and pepper until tender.
Cut up as for salad.
Saute celery and pepper in butter.
Mix with chicken and soup.
Cook rice and put in casserole dish.
Push to sides of dish and fill center with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Put in oven and heat for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
(Can be made day ahead, except for baking time.)

title: pineapple delight
directions: Drain juice off crushed pineapple (juice is not used for recipe).
Add all ingredients together in large bowl.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Pour boiling water over pickles.
Let stand until cold.
Wipe dry and put into jars.
Bring ingredients to a boil and when cool, pour over pickles.
Seal.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Flatten biscuits, filling each with about 1 tablespoon of chicken mixture.
Fold in half and seal edges.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 400° or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: chicken cheesegetti
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 9 hours.
Drain liquid into saucepan; add spaghetti.
Cook spaghetti just until tender.
Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces; add Velveeta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, chicken, chilies and soup to spaghetti.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.

title: rhubarb-pineapple crumble
directions: Thaw frozen rhubarb completely, if using, draining well.
In a large bowl, combine fresh or thawed rhubarb, pineapple and 1 cup brown sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain mixture, reserving juices. If necessary, add water to juices to equal 2/3 cup.
Place juices in a small saucepan.
Stir in cornstarch.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir into rhubarb and pineapple mixture; stir in lemon peel.
Place in 2-quart square baking dish.
In another bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup brown sugar, sugar, ginger and salt.
Mix; pour over top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach and mushroom quiche
directions: Prick crust with fork and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until golden.
Remove and cool.
Cook spinach according to directions and drain.
Press out water.
Set aside.
In large skillet, melt butter; add mushrooms and saute over low heat until soft (6 minutes).
In large mixing bowl, beat Ricotta cheese and eggs together until mixture is smooth.
Add flour, Worcestershire, salt and pepper; beat until well mixed.
Add cream and beat until smooth.
Fold in reserved spinach, mushrooms and Swiss cheese until well mixed.
Turn into crusts and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until set.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler with 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Stir frequently.

title: ham beans
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight.
Rinse and put into crock-pot or other pan along with other ingredients.
Celery and carrots may be added, if desired.
Simmer 6 to 8 hours in a crock-pot on medium or for a shorter length of time on the stove. When beans are soft, they are done.
Serve with chopped raw onions and cornbread.

title: walnut penuche fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with lightly aluminum foil.
Spread nuts in microsafe plate and cook on High for 6 to 7 minutes to toast. Melt butter in microsafe bowl.
Stir in sugar and milk until blended.
Cook, uncovered, on High 7 to 9 minutes, stirring 4 times to be sure sugar has completely dissolved and mixture has thickened.
Remove bowl to heat safe counter.
Add vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer for 3 to 4 minutes until smooth and glossy. Add walnuts and beat 1 more minute to distribute nuts evenly. Spread in pan.
Cool.
Refrigerate until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Peel off foil and cut.
Store in cool place tightly covered.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt in microwave and mix up real good with mixer. Pour on baked cake, then pour the remaining batter on top. Bake 25 minutes longer. It is good to bake the day before needed.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all together.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: orange and lemon glaze
directions: Combine orange rind, lemon rind and orange juice in small bowl; mix well.
Mix in confectioners sugar.
Pour over hot cake. Yield:
Enough for 1 pound cake, 12 servings.

title: taco flower
directions: On a serving platter, spread the 2 cans of bean dip.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread over bean dip.
Chop scallions and black olives.
Layer over sour cream mix.
Chop tomatoes and layer over onions/olives.
Cover with mixture of shredded cheeses.
Chill before serving.
Scoop up with chips.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool.
Peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and butter.
Stir occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion, and seasonings.
Fold in potatoes and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Can be frozen.

title: pineapple barbecued hens
directions: Halve hens lengthwise and remove backbones.
In a large shallow dish, combine 1/4 cup pineapple juice with remaining ingredients.
Pour over hens and marinate, refrigerated, for at least two hours.
Grill or broil according to cornish hen package directions.

title: scallops - fresh
directions: Mix flour and bread crumbs.
Roll scallops in mixture and dip in preparation of 1 beaten egg.
Roll again in crumb mixture.
Fry in hot fat or oil about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: crock-pot cheesy potato soup
directions: Put vegetables, bouillon cubes, water and butter in crock-pot. Cook on high for 1 hour.
Turn to low; cook 5 to 7 hours.
The last hour, add flour, blended with evaporated milk, and cheese.

title: spinach salad with hearts of palm
directions: Whisk first 3 ingredients in small bowl; gradually whisk in oil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover and let stand at room temperature.
Combine spinach, hearts of palm and lemon peel in bowl.
Add enough dressing to season to taste and toss gently.

title: nutty apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: wendell's favorite sugarless cake
directions: Boil raisins, dates and pineapple 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Add vegetable oil; cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients to this, adding nuts last.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mexican squash
directions: Peel squash and slice.
Cook with minced onion until tender. Drain well and place in a casserole with 4 tablespoons of butter, cheese, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Stir all ingredients.

title: baked corned beef
directions: Soak beef in water to cover, for 1/2 hour.
Place a large sheet of foil on a cookie sheet.
Remove beef from water and pat dry.
Place on foil; pour over 1/4 cup water, spices and vegetables.
Seat tightly.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread according to directions.
Cook sausage; add green pepper and onions, cooking approximately 5 minutes.
Drain well and add eggs, Parmesan cheese, and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook a few more minutes; add mushrooms.	Press out dough; put filling in and roll up, pinching ends together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add small amounts of hot water until dough forms.
Do not knead anymore than absolutely necessary. Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, margarine and corn syrup with mixer.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, or until set.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or refrigerate.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Brown chops in oil in skillet; sprinkle chops with salt, pepper and sage.
Place apples in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter; lay chops on apples.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Gently mix sour cream and Cool Whip.
Fold in dry pudding mix. Add remaining ingredients. Chill until time to serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic. Drain.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered.
I let this cook for hours on low. The longer it cooks, the better it is.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix pineapple, cream cheese, green onions, small amount of parsley and about 2 tablespoons of pecans.
Refrigerate until firm enough to form into a ball.
Roll in pecans and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat, gradually stir at least half of the mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Blend into remaining hot mixture.
Boil one minute more, remove from heat and blend in butter and vanilla.
Add coconut and pour into baked pie shell. Whip egg whites and spread over custard.
Bake until delicately browned at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: polynesian franks(microwave recipe)
directions: In 9 x 13 x 2-inch ceramic lasagne dish or glass oblong dish, place frankfurter slices and pineapple chunks.
In 4-cup glass measure, mix brown sugar and cornstarch.
Blend in pineapple juice, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
Microwave 6 minutes on High.
Stir well with wire whisk.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes more on High until thickened and clear.
Stir well.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Prepare and set aside potatoes, onion and green pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp; strain (save drippings).
In a jar with a cover, combine egg, vinegar, seasonings and 1/4 cup warm bacon grease (discard remaining grease).
Shake mixture and pour into warm skillet.
Stir gently while heating until it thickens.
Pour hot sauce over warm vegetables.
Add crumbled bacon and mix thoroughly.

title: spinach pie smith
directions: In a bowl combine spinach, onion and Swiss cheese.
Spread into bottom of deep ten-inch pie plate.
In food processor blend flour, salt, butter and baking soda until a coarse meal.
Add eggs, milk, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend.
Pour mixture over spinach.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned and puffed.

title: soft rolls
directions: Combine the ingredients and cover dough.
Let set for 1 1/2 hours.
Shape in rolls and place on greased pans.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Press each with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix butter and 3/4 of the Oreo cookies together.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk, cream cheese and pudding; pour over cookie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Put small amount of milk with chocolate pieces and cinnamon to melt.
Add rest of milk and warm. Top with whipped cream and chocolate shavings.

title: quick easy, refrigerator rolls
directions: Stir ingredients together in order given.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Roll dough on slightly floured board and cut in favorite shape.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: campin' casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven or other large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a large bowl and place ingredients in layers in order. Cover tightly and refrigerate 8 hours or more.
Serves 12.

title: lemonade drop cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter.
Continue creaming while slowly adding honey in a fine stream.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add alternately to creamed mixture along with 1/3 cup thawed lemonade.
(Dough is soft.)
Chill for 1 hour.
Drop dough from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brush hot cookies with remaining lemonade concentrate. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: believe it or not cookies
directions: Beat all together well.
Form into balls as for peanut butter cookies.
Flatten with fork and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers together; cover with salt. Let stand overnight.
Drain; add the hot peppers which have been chopped and the vinegar and spices (spices tied in cheesecloth bag) and sugar.
Allow to boil slowly until tender, about 15 minutes.
Pack tightly into hot sterilized jars and seal at once. Or bring ingredients to a boil and pack in jars, screwing bands tightly.
Process in hot water bath at simmering temperature (180°) for 15 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well.
Knead slightly.
Grease another large bowl; put dough in it and turn dough over so that both sides are greased. Cover with foil and let stand overnight on table.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix.
Place in a 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green salad
directions: Mix and let set refrigerated overnight.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put instant pudding and milk.
Mix until smooth.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler over hot, not boiling water until smooth.

title: vee vee's fudge frosting
directions: Cook mixture at rolling boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and beat until you can spread.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cover peas with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add the 2 quarts of water, ham bone, onions and seasonings.
Bring to boiling.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bone and cut off meat.
Return meat to soup; add remaining ingredients.
Cool slowly for 45 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Combine all other ingredients; cover cucumbers and onions with the liquid.
Refrigerate in a tightly covered container for 3 days before using.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: catskinner cake
directions: Cake:
Mix 1 cup sugar, eggs, coconut, buttermilk, flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla, oil and salt well mixed.
Bake in greased oblong pan 25 to 30 minutes.

title: boiled custard-microwave
directions: Place eggs, sugar and salt in a 4 cup glass measuring cup and mix until well blended.
Stir in liquid.
To make a richer sauce, I sometimes substitute half and half or whipping cream for some of the milk.
Cook in microwave on Roast for 5 to 7 minutes, or until back of spoon is coated.
Stir several times during cooking. Chill.
Sherry or rum can be used for some of the liquid.
If used, I would cut down on the vanilla.
Add the liquor after cooking about 2 minutes.
Delicious over vanilla ice cream with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: brownie meltaways
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies as directed, except stir in coconut and chopped nuts.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, 1/3 cup margarine and vanilla.
Stir in milk, 1 teaspoon at a time, until of spreading consistency.
Spread over cooled brownies.
Refrigerate until topping is firm, about 30 minutes.
Heat chocolate and 2 teaspoons margarine until melted. Drizzle evenly over topping and refrigerate until chocolate is firm, about 15 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together	and
put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° or 375° until well set or brown.

title: love cake
directions: Mix well in a dark place with dash of moonlight.
Beat it before the old man gets home.
Hold her tight and let her rest her head on your shoulder.
Look into her eyes and press her lips to yours.
Press gently but firmly.
Bake at least 1 hour, the longer the better.

title: upside down meat pie
directions: In ovenproof skillet, brown beef with celery, onion and green peppers.
Stir in salt, chili pepper and soup.
Combine biscuit mix and milk.
Roll or pat dough into circle slightly smaller than skillet.
Spread meat mixture evenly in skillet.
Top with biscuit dough.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn upside down on platter. Top with cheese slices at once.
Cut into wedges like pie and serve.

title: banana fritters
directions: Beat egg.
Mix together sugar, flour and banana until smooth. Add egg.
Drop by tablespoon in hot fat.
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sno capped brownies
directions: Bake 25
minutes at 350°.
Take from oven and cut large marshmallows in
half
and	put
on
top, cover top and bake 5 minutes
longer;
frost lightly with chocolate frosting of 1/2 stick oleo, 4 tablespoons milk, 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Melt and mix gradually;
add powdered sugar until spreading consistency.
Use 11 x 17-inch pan.

title: mom g.'s pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Grease tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil; remove from heat.
Place tea bags in water, cover and leave for 6 minutes; remove tea bags. Add spices, tied in cloth bag.
Leave for 30 minutes, covered.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: *A 16 ounce can of peeled tomatoes may be substituted.

title: ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (175°C). In a large bowl, combine the ham, pork, eggs, bread crumbs, evaporated milk, salt and ground black pepper. Mix all together well and form into a loaf. Place loaf into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° (175°C) for 90 minutes.

title: fitzpatrick potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets; set aside.
Mix other ingredients. Remove jackets from potatoes, slice and mix with all other ingredients.

title: cranberry pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs just to blend.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, butter and salt.
Sprinkle cranberries in pastry shell; pour syrup mixture over berries.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: butternut muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl, combine squash with milk, then add oil and beaten eggs.
Combine the two mixtures with as little beating as possible.
Fill 12 greased muffin tins three quarters full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Add other ingredients like raisins, chopped nuts, spices, etc.

title: old witch magic nut cake
directions: Beat together eggs, pumpkin, oil and water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour the batter into a buttered 1 pound coffee can and place in oven standing up.
Bake at 350° for an hour and 15 minutes or until an inserted straw comes out clean. Cool cake, turn on its side and frost.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric, cinnamon and salt to a boil.
Add chopped items to the boiling mixture.
Boil on medium for 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: enchiladas
